{"term": "2010", "caseName": "Brown v. Plata", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/2010/09-1233", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - November 30, 2010", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/roberts6/oral_argument_audio/21480", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "09-1233, Schwarzenegger versus Plata, and the related cases, Mr. Phillips.", "start": 0, "stop": 7.821, "duration": 7.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court.", "start": 7.821, "stop": 10.846, "duration": 3.03}, {"text": "What this Court has under review today is an extraordinary and unprecedented order issued by a three-judge District Court, requiring the release of between 36,000 and 45,000 inmates, currently incarcerated in the California penal system within a two-year period.", "start": 10.846, "stop": 31.721, "duration": 20.88}, {"text": "The order in this particular case is made particularly remarkable because it strikes me that at a minimum it is extraordinarily premature.", "start": 31.721, "stop": 41.496, "duration": 9.78}, {"text": "That it may come at some point in this process that an order, probably substantially smaller in scope than this one, may become appropriate, but if this is supposed to be an order or remedy of last resort, and what the district court has done here is leapfrogged a series of steps that should have been taken ahead of going this particular route.", "start": 41.496, "stop": 62.179, "duration": 20.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "One case, Mr. Phillips, is pending for 20 years, is that not so?", "start": 62.179, "stop": 67.052, "duration": 4.87}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes that is correct, Justice Ginsburg.", "start": 67.052, "stop": 68.939, "duration": 1.89}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "So it seems to me -- and there were something like 70 orders from the district court, the single-judge district court in that case?", "start": 68.939, "stop": 81.026, "duration": 12.09}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is absolutely true, Justice Ginsburg.", "start": 81.026, "stop": 82.47, "duration": 1.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "And no change, so how much longer do we have to wait, another 20 years?", "start": 82.47, "stop": 86.809, "duration": 4.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Justice Ginsburg.", "start": 86.809, "stop": 87.706, "duration": 0.9}, {"text": "I think, obviously, the length of time you have to wait in some ways depends on what the state of the remedial phase is in the particular case.", "start": 87.706, "stop": 95.41, "duration": 7.7}, {"text": "And in this case and in recognition, frankly, of the substantial problems that were inherent in the penal system as it existed during the 1990s and up until the early 2000s, a receiver was appointed, specifically in the Plata class, but there was also a connection between the receiver and the special master even in the Coleman class before the three-judge panel was convened.", "start": 95.41, "stop": 120.921, "duration": 25.51}, {"text": "And under those circumstances and given the extraordinary powers that the receiver had been accorded, what should have -- the most logical course if this is supposed to be a remedy of last resort was to allow the receiver an opportunity to implement the extraordinary powers that were conferred upon him, and then see, because if it turns out that we are making progress –", "start": 120.921, "stop": 143.045, "duration": 22.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Excuse me, could you tell me from your briefs, I just haven't understood what the alternative steps are?", "start": 143.045, "stop": 151.432, "duration": 8.39}, {"text": "The court below talked about some proposals like construction and said the legislature has struck them down.", "start": 151.432, "stop": 160.667, "duration": 9.24}, {"text": "There's -- the fiscal crisis has gotten worse, so construction is really not an option.", "start": 160.667, "stop": 166.527, "duration": 5.86}, {"text": "I don't see how you wait for an option that doesn't exist.", "start": 166.527, "stop": 171.217, "duration": 4.69}, {"text": "They talked about hiring more staff, but the conclusion was that even if you maximize the staff, you don't have the facilities to add more staff, which is what you need to cure the constitutional violation.", "start": 171.217, "stop": 186.094, "duration": 14.88}, {"text": "So tell me what specific steps outside of this order should have been given time to be implemented because the receiver has basically said, “I've tried, and the small progress we made has been reversed because the population just keeps growing.", "start": 186.094, "stop": 206.518, "duration": 20.42}, {"text": "So we can never get ahead of the problem.”", "start": 206.518, "stop": 208.781, "duration": 2.26}, {"text": "So slow down from the rhetoric and give me concrete –", "start": 208.781, "stop": 213.647, "duration": 4.87}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sure.", "start": 213.647, "stop": 214.45, "duration": 0.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- details about what the least restrictive means would have been other than to say, throw it back to a receiver and special master who are saying, we don't have a solution outside of reducing overcrowding.", "start": 214.45, "stop": 227.008, "duration": 12.56}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- I don't think that's a fair characterization of what the receiver said.", "start": 227.008, "stop": 229.817, "duration": 2.81}, {"text": "The receiver said that at any population he would in fact get you --", "start": 229.817, "stop": 233.108, "duration": 3.29}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, Counsel that was one statement years ago.", "start": 233.108, "stop": 237.552, "duration": 4.44}, {"text": "Is that is all you are relying on?", "start": 237.552, "stop": 238.988, "duration": 1.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, no.", "start": 238.988, "stop": 239.312, "duration": 0.32}, {"text": "That's not all I'm relying on.", "start": 239.312, "stop": 240.221, "duration": 0.91}, {"text": "All I'm suggesting --", "start": 240.221, "stop": 240.501, "duration": 0.28}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "That may be your weakest argument.", "start": 240.501, "stop": 241.693, "duration": 1.19}, {"text": "Tell me -- give me concrete steps that are least -- less restrictive.", "start": 241.693, "stop": 246.064, "duration": 4.37}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well if you -- all you have to do is look at what the receiver has done over the course of the period of time since his appointment, and particularly when the second receiver was put in place.", "start": 246.064, "stop": 255.772, "duration": 9.71}, {"text": "First of all, A.B. 900 has been enacted.", "start": 255.772, "stop": 258.392, "duration": 2.62}, {"text": "There is significant construction.", "start": 258.392, "stop": 259.993, "duration": 1.6}, {"text": "There has been ground broken.", "start": 259.993, "stop": 261.776, "duration": 1.78}, {"text": "There are substantial facilities in place.", "start": 261.776, "stop": 264.391, "duration": 2.62}, {"text": "Second, the receiver has had extraordinary success in the hiring process.", "start": 264.391, "stop": 269.723, "duration": 5.33}, {"text": "We are at close to 90 percent --", "start": 269.723, "stop": 271.104, "duration": 1.38}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there in fact less overcrowding because I thought what this case was all about was that the receiver has said, the special master has said, “we can't make any progress at all until there are fewer people; we have no place to put clinics.", "start": 271.104, "stop": 288.835, "duration": 17.73}, {"text": "The first step, not the last step, but given what we are dealing with here, the potential first step, is that we have fewer people so there is more room for these health facilities, more room for staff to operate.”", "start": 288.835, "stop": 307.198, "duration": 18.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Ginsburg, the fundamental issue in this case seems to me as -- what is the real cause of the constitutional violation here?", "start": 307.198, "stop": 314.086, "duration": 6.89}, {"text": "And the real cause of the constitutional violation here has always been the culture of disregard for the inmates.", "start": 314.086, "stop": 320.891, "duration": 6.81}, {"text": "What the receiver was put in place for, the reason he was appointed, and properly so, this was with the State's consent, this is not over our objection, was to change that fundamental culture and to provide, one; construction, to provide increased numbers, to provide --", "start": 320.891, "stop": 336.817, "duration": 15.93}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But he can't provide construction when the State doesn't supply the money for it?", "start": 336.817, "stop": 341.802, "duration": 4.99}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Except that since the August 8, 2008, period of time, you know, literally hundreds of millions of dollars have gone to construction specifically and more than $4 billion have been spent on the provision of healthcare in this particular system and a great deal of that is because of the receiver.", "start": 341.802, "stop": 362.673, "duration": 20.87}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then if there are -- if there are these great changes in circumstances so that now they -- medical care can be administered in something approaching a decent way, you could go back to the single-judge district court and say I'm moving under 60(b); circumstances have changed, it is no longer the case that it's impossible to render decent health care.", "start": 362.673, "stop": 395.022, "duration": 32.35}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Ginsburg, I don't think we could get that relief from the single-judge district court, unless you are asking me to actually seek to remove the entirety of the claim.", "start": 395.022, "stop": 403.22, "duration": 8.2}, {"text": "I mean, the order that says that we have to get to 137.5 percent of the design, the designed capacity within two years is a three-judge district court decision.", "start": 403.22, "stop": 413.115, "duration": 9.89}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So you go back to that panel because it invited you to. It said if circumstances change, come back.", "start": 413.115, "stop": 419.818, "duration": 6.7}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, but that will always be the case, Justice Sotomayor.", "start": 419.818, "stop": 422.357, "duration": 2.54}, {"text": "The fundamental question here is, Congress shifted dramatically, the approach that you are supposed to take as a court of equity in this context, this is supposed to be a matter of last resort, which would mean that you would give the receiver a full opportunity to do what the receiver--", "start": 422.357, "stop": 437.461, "duration": 15.1}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What the receiver said the best statement that seemed to me to summarize it.", "start": 437.461, "stop": 442.512, "duration": 5.05}, {"text": "It's in his brief on page 9.", "start": 442.512, "stop": 445.309, "duration": 2.8}, {"text": "He has about two paragraphs and as you read that two paragraphs, it sounds as if overcrowding is a big, big cause of this problem, which is horrendous, which if you think it's accurately described in the mental case in the first page, two paragraphs, if that's a fair description from the record, it's a horrendous problem.", "start": 445.309, "stop": 466.665, "duration": 21.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well --", "start": 466.665, "stop": 466.97, "duration": 0.31}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What the receiver says is overcrowding is a big cause of it and then he says, “I think we have discovered you actually can provide care, and certainly our plan and turnaround plan believes we can provide constitutional levels of care, no matter what the population is.”", "start": 466.97, "stop": 481.674, "duration": 14.7}, {"text": "So then you look to the care and turnaround plan and it says, “spend $8 billion building more buildings and then the legislature rejected it.”", "start": 481.674, "stop": 490.727, "duration": 9.05}, {"text": "Okay?", "start": 490.727, "stop": 491.667, "duration": 0.94}, {"text": "Now, there we are.", "start": 491.667, "stop": 492.391, "duration": 0.72}, {"text": "More time, what's supposed to happen?", "start": 492.391, "stop": 493.839, "duration": 1.45}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, but, Justice Breyer, the legislature also approved a smaller, but nevertheless multibillion-dollar construction program.", "start": 493.839, "stop": 499.372, "duration": 5.53}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was 2.31 or something like that.", "start": 499.372, "stop": 501.097, "duration": 1.72}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I –", "start": 501.097, "stop": 502.006, "duration": 0.91}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "And did they approve the 2.3?", "start": 502.006, "stop": 503.449, "duration": 1.44}, {"text": "Is that in place, 2.35?", "start": 503.449, "stop": 505.353, "duration": 1.9}, {"text": "Did they approve that?", "start": 505.353, "stop": 506.315, "duration": 0.96}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, they did approve that --", "start": 506.315, "stop": 506.867, "duration": 0.55}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Okay.", "start": 506.867, "stop": 507.416, "duration": 0.55}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and that money is being spent.", "start": 507.416, "stop": 507.735, "duration": 0.32}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "So he said, “we need eight, we need eight and they approved 2.35.”", "start": 507.735, "stop": 512.683, "duration": 4.95}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, and the receiver --", "start": 512.683, "stop": 513.378, "duration": 0.7}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there any evidence here that suggests that 2.35 is sufficient to cure the constitutional violation?", "start": 513.378, "stop": 519.491, "duration": 6.11}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I don't know whether it will get you there or not --", "start": 519.491, "stop": 521.107, "duration": 1.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "So I take it from your answer the answer is no, there is no evidence?", "start": 521.107, "stop": 523.76, "duration": 2.65}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there is the evidence that the receiver asked for contempt for not getting the 8 billion and withdrew that motion, so obviously there is some sense in which the receiver is reasonably satisfied with 2.35 billion as an opening gambit.", "start": 523.76, "stop": 538.07, "duration": 14.31}, {"text": "But again, all of this goes to what is, at least from my perspective, the fundamental question the court should have evaluated in the first instance, which is, are we ready yet to give up hope at this point?", "start": 538.07, "stop": 549.912, "duration": 11.84}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what he says -- what the receiver says about the 2.35, is that it is a significant step farther. It is certainly better than no construction at all.", "start": 549.912, "stop": 559.535, "duration": 9.62}, {"text": "However, that is not equivalent to a conclusion that that current compromise will result in sustainable constitutional healthcare at current population density levels.", "start": 559.535, "stop": 570.958, "duration": 11.42}, {"text": "That's what he said about it.", "start": 570.958, "stop": 572.597, "duration": 1.64}, {"text": "So we have his views and I'm back to my question, what else is supposed to happen, which was your question initially?", "start": 572.597, "stop": 581.584, "duration": 8.99}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Breyer, when the receiver says that, now remember he says at current population levels, he doesn't suggest, and his brief is very clear that it doesn't urge this Court to affirm the particular order in this case.", "start": 581.584, "stop": 595.812, "duration": 14.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr.--", "start": 595.812, "stop": 597.088, "duration": 1.28}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can I just finish this?", "start": 597.088, "stop": 598.434, "duration": 1.35}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 598.434, "stop": 599.034, "duration": 0.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the reality is that the population levels have dropped pretty significantly since August, since the trial in this particular case and given the actions by the legislature in AB 18 and the actions of the legislature in AB 900, there are both a lot of expenditures on the table and substantial reductions in the population size, and so therefore, even under the receiver's --", "start": 599.034, "stop": 622.636, "duration": 23.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do we have information about that substantial reduction?", "start": 622.636, "stop": 626.239, "duration": 3.6}, {"text": "I mean, in this record, it just seems to be that it's -- no matter how many efforts have been made, the population goes up and now you say that the population has gone down; from what point in time and how much has it gone down?", "start": 626.239, "stop": 646.198, "duration": 19.96}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it's down to around, as I understand it, about 147,000 from a high of around 165 to 170,000, and it has dropped, as we know, because there has been a change in the good time credits.", "start": 646.198, "stop": 658.679, "duration": 12.48}, {"text": "There has been a significant number of transfers.", "start": 658.679, "stop": 661.25, "duration": 2.57}, {"text": "I mean, that was the purpose of the governor's proclamation (Voice Overlap).", "start": 661.25, "stop": 664.127, "duration": 2.88}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So it's possible that within the two-year period, you are going to hit the mark, if you -- that's what --", "start": 664.127, "stop": 670.721, "duration": 6.59}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think it unlikely.", "start": 670.721, "stop": 671.536, "duration": 0.81}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- that's what the three-judge panel said, which is if you implement most of the proposals being made, you are likely to hit the mark.", "start": 671.536, "stop": 681.364, "duration": 9.83}, {"text": "So what you are saying is you are going to do it and if you don't, they invited you to come back and -- you really don't think that if you hit 140 percentage, that the court is going to order an immediate release of the 2.5 percent over the limit it set?", "start": 681.364, "stop": 699.631, "duration": 18.27}, {"text": "It's going to ask you, “What have you put into place to reach that level over what additional period of time?”", "start": 699.631, "stop": 706.662, "duration": 7.03}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is a core sort of federalism answer and then a basic sort of factual point to be made here.", "start": 706.662, "stop": 712.45, "duration": 5.79}, {"text": "Let me make the second one first, and then I want to come back to the, what you may regard as rhetorical, but nevertheless I think important, which is that when we made our initial proposal to the three-judge court, suggesting what we thought would be a reasonable reduction within a reasonable period of time, it was met with both a motion for contempt and summary rejection out of hand, notwithstanding that there was improvement in both --", "start": 712.45, "stop": 732.207, "duration": 19.76}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So what are we fighting about?", "start": 732.207, "stop": 733.786, "duration": 1.58}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "So --", "start": 733.786, "stop": 733.955, "duration": 0.17}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are we fighting about that the plan was wrong or are we fighting about that you are angry that you were told to do it in two years -- in 22 years, as opposed to do it in 25 years?", "start": 733.955, "stop": 748.091, "duration": 14.14}, {"text": "Is that -- is that what you're objecting to?", "start": 748.091, "stop": 749.553, "duration": 1.46}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 749.553, "stop": 749.75, "duration": 0.2}, {"text": "I think this -- this goes to the federalism point.", "start": 749.75, "stop": 752.406, "duration": 2.66}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can you do it in 5 years?", "start": 752.406, "stop": 754.663, "duration": 2.26}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know.", "start": 754.663, "stop": 755.236, "duration": 0.57}, {"text": "I -- you know, if -- balancing all of the policies that the State has to take into account, can it get there and is that in the best interest of the State of California, if it is, yes, then we can get there.", "start": 755.236, "stop": 764.133, "duration": 8.9}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the best interest of the State of California, isn't it to deliver adequate constitutional care to the people that it incarcerates?", "start": 764.133, "stop": 773.509, "duration": 9.38}, {"text": "That's a constitutional obligation.", "start": 773.509, "stop": 775.514, "duration": 2}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Absolutely!", "start": 775.514, "stop": 776.178, "duration": 0.66}, {"text": "And California recognizes that.", "start": 776.178, "stop": 777.216, "duration": 1.04}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So when are you going to get to that?", "start": 777.216, "stop": 779.246, "duration": 2.03}, {"text": "What are you going to avoid the needless deaths that were reported in this record?", "start": 779.246, "stop": 784.821, "duration": 5.58}, {"text": "When are you going to avoid or get around people sitting in their feces for days in a dazed state?", "start": 784.821, "stop": 794.403, "duration": 9.58}, {"text": "When are you going to get to a point where you are going to deliver care that is going to be adequate?", "start": 794.403, "stop": 798.88, "duration": 4.48}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "But don't be rhetorical.", "start": 798.88, "stop": 801.073, "duration": 2.19}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'll do my best.", "start": 801.073, "stop": 801.833, "duration": 0.76}, {"text": "Thank you, Your Honor. [Laughter]", "start": 801.833, "stop": 803.046, "duration": 1.21}, {"text": "I mean, first of all, if you look at the receiver's 2009 death review which came out in September 2010, it specifically says that there has been a significant downward trend over the past 4 years.", "start": 803.046, "stop": 813.592, "duration": 10.55}, {"text": "The suicides -- the 25 suicides in 2009 were 66 percent of the average for the preceding 3 years, and the 9 homicides were 60 percent of the average.", "start": 813.592, "stop": 821.775, "duration": 8.18}, {"text": "There have been significant improvements.", "start": 821.775, "stop": 823.777, "duration": 2}, {"text": "And the more important point in response to your specific question, Justice Sotomayor, is that the record in this case was cut off in August of 2008, and so what we have are --", "start": 823.777, "stop": 833.453, "duration": 9.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of course, but the problem I have with that, Mr. Phillips, is that at some point the Court has to say, “You have been given enough time, the constitutional violation still persists as the State itself acknowledges” –", "start": 833.453, "stop": 849.558, "duration": 16.11}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I'm not sure we've--", "start": 849.558, "stop": 851.336, "duration": 1.78}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- “overcrowding is the principal -- overcrowding is the principal cause, as experts have testified, and it's now time for a remedy.", "start": 851.336, "stop": 858.277, "duration": 6.94}, {"text": "The Court can't -- has to at some point focus on the remedy, and that's what it did, and that it seems to me was a perfectly reasonable decision.", "start": 858.277, "stop": 866.691, "duration": 8.41}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Justice Kennedy, I agree with everything you say except -- and I even agree with the last statement because, you know, you needed a significant remedy, there's no question about it, but you got a significant remedy when the receiver was appointed in 2005 and implemented a program in 2006.", "start": 866.691, "stop": 882.598, "duration": 15.91}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "How much time do you think the receiver needed?", "start": 882.598, "stop": 884.938, "duration": 2.34}, {"text": "I mean, how much time did -- should the court have given the receiver to develop his plan and to try to implement his plan?", "start": 884.938, "stop": 892.173, "duration": 7.24}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there's no -- Justice Kagan, there is no specific time frame.", "start": 892.173, "stop": 894.885, "duration": 2.71}, {"text": "I mean, obviously we believe that we are entitled to a reasonable opportunity to comply with the receiver's orders and to bring ourselves ultimately into compliance with the Constitution, and --", "start": 894.885, "stop": 903.147, "duration": 8.26}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, at some point the State itself said that if it had I think seven years, it could get down to 137.5, and didn't seem to object to that?", "start": 903.147, "stop": 912.164, "duration": 9.02}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, that's -- Justice Kennedy, you know, given all of the other constraints, et cetera -- again, there is a fundamental difference between what you do under the hammer of a district court order, which is what we have under these circumstances, and what the State will do.", "start": 912.164, "stop": 927.56, "duration": 15.4}, {"text": "That said, the State is absolutely committed.", "start": 927.56, "stop": 929.911, "duration": 2.35}, {"text": "I mean the -- again, to go back to what is the root cause of the constitutional violation, it's not overcrowding.", "start": 929.911, "stop": 936.576, "duration": 6.67}, {"text": "I mean, when California violated the constitutional rights of the mentally ill in the 1990s, the prisons weren't crowded.", "start": 936.576, "stop": 943.513, "duration": 6.94}, {"text": "It was because there was a fundamental lack of attentiveness to medical care under those circumstances and that is unfortunate, to be sure more than that.", "start": 943.513, "stop": 952.401, "duration": 8.89}, {"text": "But that was the reason, to go back to your point, Justice Kennedy, that's why the, receiver, which is an extraordinary remedy, to confer upon a private individual the entire authority to run the California Department of Corrections, not just simply a facility or anything like that, but the entire Department of Corrections' medical health provision, is incredible.", "start": 952.401, "stop": 973.475, "duration": 21.07}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But I thought that officer himself said, “I can't do this without as a first step reducing the population.", "start": 973.475, "stop": 984.195, "duration": 10.72}, {"text": "Nothing else is going to work until we reduce the population to the point where there is room for clinics, room for medical personnel to operate.”", "start": 984.195, "stop": 997.685, "duration": 13.49}, {"text": "I mean, that was the view of the district judge, the special master in one case, the receiver in the other case, everybody, they all agreed reducing the population is not going to cure it, not going to make everything perfect, but without doing that as a first step, nothing -- there will be no cure.", "start": 997.685, "stop": 1023.254, "duration": 25.57}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, Justice Ginsburg, even if you accept that, and I don't think that's precisely how I would interpret what the receiver said under these circumstances anyway, but even if you accept that, the idea of a 137.5 percent designed cap that has to be implemented within fewer than two years is a remedy that is neither necessary nor sufficient and is not aimed at the specific class.", "start": 1023.254, "stop": 1048.654, "duration": 25.4}, {"text": "It doesn't remedy the specific Federal rights as required by the Prisoners Litigation Reform Act.", "start": 1048.654, "stop": 1054.053, "duration": 5.4}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't get the class thing, because what -- you can't have a remedy just limited to the class.", "start": 1054.053, "stop": 1062.027, "duration": 7.97}, {"text": "The class wants to have clinics.", "start": 1062.027, "stop": 1064.687, "duration": 2.66}, {"text": "They want to have personnel who function someplace outside of a broom closet.", "start": 1064.687, "stop": 1070.511, "duration": 5.82}, {"text": "So you can't deal with this problem by just dealing with the mentally ill and the people with medical problems.", "start": 1070.511, "stop": 1078.024, "duration": 7.51}, {"text": "You have to provide space for facilities.", "start": 1078.024, "stop": 1082.799, "duration": 4.78}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think, Justice Ginsburg, the -- the fundamental point here is that it may eventually be that you have to get to that stage, but if you look at the receiver's reports since August 2008, which consistently analyzed this issue, and they say, “we have been able successfully to bring in very qualified personnel, and we have significantly larger numbers.", "start": 1082.799, "stop": 1104.488, "duration": 21.69}, {"text": "We know there is construction in place.", "start": 1104.488, "stop": 1106.371, "duration": 1.88}, {"text": "It may not be as substantial as what I originally proposed, it is nevertheless very significant” and Congress was very explicit that the remedy of a prisoner release order should be the remedy of --", "start": 1106.371, "stop": 1119.119, "duration": 12.75}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where do I look at to find this?", "start": 1119.119, "stop": 1121.068, "duration": 1.95}, {"text": "It's a big record.", "start": 1121.068, "stop": 1122.499, "duration": 1.43}, {"text": "What I did was I -- it refers to on-line evidence and I went and looked at the pictures, and the pictures are pretty horrendous to me and I would say page 10 of the religious group's brief, for example, shows you one of them and what they are saying is, it's -- it's obvious, just look at it.", "start": 1122.499, "stop": 1141.505, "duration": 19.01}, {"text": "You cannot have mental health facilities that will stop people from killing themselves and you cannot have medical facilities that will stop staph and tubercular infection in conditions like this and then you look at them and you've looked at them.", "start": 1141.505, "stop": 1158.003, "duration": 16.5}, {"text": "I have looked at them and what is the answer to that?", "start": 1158.003, "stop": 1162.116, "duration": 4.11}, {"text": "There is nothing in here that -- the special master said $8 billion is the answer, and they haven't come close.", "start": 1162.116, "stop": 1170.611, "duration": 8.5}, {"text": "So how can I or you if you were in my position, what would you say in an opinion that says that these three judges who have 200 pages of findings, what would you say to, to -- as an answer to what I just said?", "start": 1170.611, "stop": 1187.112, "duration": 16.5}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would say that the Prisoners Litigation Reform Act has a series of very specific requirements that the Federal court has to comply with and that in deciding to go to the three-judge district court in the first instance, you have to examine the orders that are in place and whether those orders have had a reasonable time within which to operate.", "start": 1187.112, "stop": 1206.379, "duration": 19.27}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, but the State -- the State did not claim that either order in either case has succeeded in achieving the remedy.", "start": 1206.379, "stop": 1215.128, "duration": 8.75}, {"text": "You have never claimed that.", "start": 1215.128, "stop": 1217.545, "duration": 2.42}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it depends on what you mean by --", "start": 1217.545, "stop": 1219.273, "duration": 1.73}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And -- and -- and just if I can have your attention for a moment, I have this problem with the case.", "start": 1219.273, "stop": 1226.321, "duration": 7.05}, {"text": "Overcrowding is of course always the cause.", "start": 1226.321, "stop": 1229.358, "duration": 3.04}, {"text": "If I am running a hotel -- if I am looking at a highway system, I need a highway, what's the number of cars?", "start": 1229.358, "stop": 1234.727, "duration": 5.37}, {"text": "If the problem is bad service in a hotel, well, it's the number of employees per -- per guest.", "start": 1234.727, "stop": 1238.867, "duration": 4.14}, {"text": "I mean, that's fairly simple.", "start": 1238.867, "stop": 1240.526, "duration": 1.66}, {"text": "Now, I recognize of course that Congress has -- had imposed a special duty on us, but I think it means that overcrowding must not be ordered unless that is the only efficacious remedy in -- in a permissible period of time and it seems to me there is massive expert testimony to support that proposition on the part of the prisoners.", "start": 1240.526, "stop": 1265.478, "duration": 24.95}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I mean, it seems to me that, first of all, I'm not sure that is consistent with the language, that’s primary cause of the constitutional violation, not the primary impediment to the implementation of a specific remedy.", "start": 1265.478, "stop": 1276.683, "duration": 11.2}, {"text": "So I think that is still a difficult and open question as to how to proceed, but it still strikes me that the sequence that Congress envisions and the one that would make the most sense and ultimately the one that hopefully would accommodate both the plaintiffs' interests and the State's interests, and the Department of Corrections' interests, is to allow the receiver to stay on a course that candidly I think will in fact get you there.", "start": 1276.683, "stop": 1301.153, "duration": 24.47}, {"text": "I mean, again, one of the real flaws in this case, Justice Kennedy, is nobody doubts for a moment that there have been very significant violations of constitutional rights years gone by, and indeed a failure on the mental health side ultimately to get you -- get to the point where we are in fact providing a significant remedy.", "start": 1301.153, "stop": 1320.32, "duration": 19.17}, {"text": "The reality is that in the course of the last three to four years under the guidance of the -- of the receiver, who coordinates with the special master on the mental health side, and does it with the cooperation of the State of California, there have been significant -- there has been significant movement in the right direction and if the court had not jumped the gun and said, look, we're not going to -- we're not going to let that part play itself out, we are going to leap ahead and go to a three-judge court and go to the prisons with the prisoner release order, this process would have played itself out and we wouldn't be here --", "start": 1320.32, "stop": 1352.331, "duration": 32.01}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "All this talk about what the receiver may think can be done seems a little bit perplexing to me because the receiver did not testify before the three-judge court, isn't that correct?", "start": 1352.331, "stop": 1364.966, "duration": 12.63}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "That -- that is true, Justice Alito.", "start": 1364.966, "stop": 1365.748, "duration": 0.78}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "You were not allowed to question him?", "start": 1365.748, "stop": 1367.561, "duration": 1.81}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "We were not allowed to --", "start": 1367.561, "stop": 1368.47, "duration": 0.91}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "And now he has submitted what is styled in amicus brief where he doesn't address issues of law.", "start": 1368.47, "stop": 1376.163, "duration": 7.69}, {"text": "He explains his views about -- he tries to explain prior statements and supplement those prior statements.", "start": 1376.163, "stop": 1384.085, "duration": 7.92}, {"text": "Is that proper?", "start": 1384.085, "stop": 1386.347, "duration": 2.26}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, you know, I'm a long-time believer that amicus briefs is pretty much open season in terms of anything you want to present on them, but I mean, obviously I think it’s --", "start": 1386.347, "stop": 1394.235, "duration": 7.89}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that true?", "start": 1394.235, "stop": 1394.676, "duration": 0.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- clearly a better system –", "start": 1394.676, "stop": 1396.038, "duration": 1.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can a witness testify -- can a witness submit an amicus brief that consists of an affidavit?", "start": 1396.038, "stop": 1401.298, "duration": 5.26}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor, that's obviously not appropriate and it's one of the things that we've complained about.", "start": 1401.298, "stop": 1404.715, "duration": 3.42}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "I thought the -- the -- that brief was filed because the -- there were, in your presentations there were representations about the special master, and he filed that brief to say, “You must understand this in context, I was making a speech at the club,” but he wanted to put in context what you had used.", "start": 1404.715, "stop": 1429.487, "duration": 24.77}, {"text": "You had quoted his statements.", "start": 1429.487, "stop": 1432.072, "duration": 2.58}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, to be sure, although, candidly, we had -- we had referred to some of those same statements even in the jurisdictional statement in this litigation.", "start": 1432.072, "stop": 1439.318, "duration": 7.25}, {"text": "Those have been part of the case for quite some time.", "start": 1439.318, "stop": 1441.855, "duration": 2.54}, {"text": "So I -- I don't know what motivated the special master to file an out-of-time brief -- or I mean, the receiver to file an out-of-time brief, but I understand -- but you know, we didn't object to it so long as the court was of a mind to hear from the receiver.", "start": 1441.855, "stop": 1454.536, "duration": 12.68}, {"text": "But I do think the most important part of that though to keep in mind in this context is the receiver didn't ask for this Court to affirm.", "start": 1454.536, "stop": 1461.55, "duration": 7.01}, {"text": "The receiver simply clarified certain statements that had been made and tried to say, as Justice Alito described, put them into some kind of context and that's -- and that's fine, and we obviously don't have any quarrel with -- with that particular presentation.", "start": 1461.55, "stop": 1474.348, "duration": 12.8}, {"text": "But I do think to say that the receiver has insisted that he cannot get to a constitutionally permissible result without the order that has been imposed in this particular case is -- is simply not consistent with either the record and it's certainly not consistent with that amicus brief.", "start": 1474.348, "stop": 1490.77, "duration": 16.42}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but the experts testified to that effect?", "start": 1490.77, "stop": 1493.96, "duration": 3.19}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I mean, experts may -- certainly reached that specific conclusion, but this Court has recognized --", "start": 1493.96, "stop": 1498.891, "duration": 4.93}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the strike force and the governor's -- governor's commission reached the same conclusion?", "start": 1498.891, "stop": 1504.117, "duration": 5.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well --", "start": 1504.117, "stop": 1504.405, "duration": 0.29}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "The strike team, I think they called them.", "start": 1504.405, "stop": 1506.037, "duration": 1.63}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, but again, it seems to me that there is a very, very, very big difference between what do you need to accomplish in order to remedy whatever -- whatever the constitutional violation is, recognizing in the first instance that the biggest element of an Eighth Amendment violation is the deliberate indifference prong, which absolutely seems to me to have been completely eliminated by the conduct of the State over the course of the last three to four years.", "start": 1506.037, "stop": 1529.266, "duration": 23.23}, {"text": "There is no evidence –", "start": 1529.266, "stop": 1529.995, "duration": 0.73}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What specifically will happen?", "start": 1529.995, "stop": 1531.852, "duration": 1.86}, {"text": "I mean, at the moment, you know, we could go through, we have all these briefs, I mean there are all these experts, all the reports.", "start": 1531.852, "stop": 1538.232, "duration": 6.38}, {"text": "Everybody is saying you need to spend the money and we have -- if you really want to cure the constitutional violation, we have the legislature rejecting 8 billion but 2, which doesn't -- 2.35, and so -- nothing, and a void and give us more time.", "start": 1538.232, "stop": 1555.993, "duration": 17.76}, {"text": "I mean, I read the newspaper.", "start": 1555.993, "stop": 1557.019, "duration": 1.03}, {"text": "It doesn't seem to me California has been voting a lot of money for new programs.", "start": 1557.019, "stop": 1561.462, "duration": 4.44}, {"text": "The -- the -- what is it -- what is it specifically that would happen that would cure this problem were we to say -- I mean, a big human rights problem -- what would we say -- what would happen if we were to say, no, this panel's wrong?", "start": 1561.462, "stop": 1578.244, "duration": 16.78}, {"text": "What would happen that would cure the problem?", "start": 1578.244, "stop": 1580.44, "duration": 2.2}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it depends I suppose on some ways on how you --", "start": 1580.44, "stop": 1582.39, "duration": 1.95}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "A constitutional problem which the State itself admits is constitutional, a State with a governor who has said publicly that there is this tremendous safety and health problem in the prisons.", "start": 1582.39, "stop": 1594.192, "duration": 11.8}, {"text": "What -- what would happen?", "start": 1594.192, "stop": 1595.528, "duration": 1.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, if the Court were to conclude that the three-judge panel shouldn't have been convened, that would be one outcome.", "start": 1595.528, "stop": 1601.356, "duration": 5.83}, {"text": "If the Court concludes that it was appropriate to convene it, but 137.5 percent is not narrowly tailored, it would be a different one.", "start": 1601.356, "stop": 1606.969, "duration": 5.61}, {"text": "Either way, it will go back obviously to a court of equity.", "start": 1606.969, "stop": 1610.625, "duration": 3.66}, {"text": "The receiver is in place.", "start": 1610.625, "stop": 1612.143, "duration": 1.52}, {"text": "The receiver has a comprehensive plan in place which he is implementing as we speak.", "start": 1612.143, "stop": 1617.589, "duration": 5.45}, {"text": "One of the things that --", "start": 1617.589, "stop": 1618.205, "duration": 0.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "One piece of it -- you said something about the 2.35 million, they didn't come up with the 8 million, but they did come up with the 2.35 billion and then I'm just looking at this brief for the receiver and there is a footnote, page 11, footnote 3, that says, “No, that money isn't there.", "start": 1618.205, "stop": 1640.933, "duration": 22.73}, {"text": "It is dependent upon several approvals that have not yet been secured and such approvals ultimately may not be forthcoming.”", "start": 1640.933, "stop": 1653.758, "duration": 12.83}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, 400 million of it has already been spent.", "start": 1653.758, "stop": 1656.137, "duration": 2.38}, {"text": "The rest of it has already been earmarked for this particular purpose, and there is -- and the expectation from the State of California is that money is going forward.", "start": 1656.137, "stop": 1665.084, "duration": 8.95}, {"text": "Construction is, as we speak, under way and the one thing we do know is that every time the receiver asks for a check he gets one.", "start": 1665.084, "stop": 1670.747, "duration": 5.66}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But not the 2.35?", "start": 1670.747, "stop": 1672.537, "duration": 1.79}, {"text": "I mean, I think you did say earlier that this was a done deal, 2.35 billion, but this is a note telling us it's not so.", "start": 1672.537, "stop": 1683.179, "duration": 10.64}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the receiver is saying it's not etched in stone.", "start": 1683.179, "stop": 1686.234, "duration": 3.05}, {"text": "I understand that, but our assumption and our expectation and our belief is that that money is going to be used for construction.", "start": 1686.234, "stop": 1695.528, "duration": 9.29}, {"text": "There are projects that are finished.", "start": 1695.528, "stop": 1697.186, "duration": 1.66}, {"text": "There are projects that are underway, and there are projects that are scheduled to begin within the next six weeks, all of which will be funded out of that $2.35 billion.", "start": 1697.186, "stop": 1705.791, "duration": 8.61}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "And one project that the joint legislative budget committee said, no, we are not going to give you money for that.", "start": 1705.791, "stop": 1712.497, "duration": 6.71}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "They asked for additional information, to be sure, but the expectation, again, from the governor, both from this governor and the governor-elect, is that that money will ultimately be approved and that that facility would be built and we are moving along very rapidly to get that construction under way, because we are talking about enormous facilities under these particular circumstances, Justice Ginsburg.", "start": 1712.497, "stop": 1732.675, "duration": 20.18}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Phillips, my trouble listening to you is that it seems as though you are asking us to re-find facts.", "start": 1732.675, "stop": 1741.76, "duration": 9.09}, {"text": "You know, you have these judges who have been involved in these cases since the beginning, for 20 years in the Plata case, who thought, we've done everything we can.", "start": 1741.76, "stop": 1751.673, "duration": 9.91}, {"text": "The receiver has done everything he can.", "start": 1751.673, "stop": 1754.385, "duration": 2.71}, {"text": "This just isn't going anywhere and it won't go anywhere until we can address this root cause of the problem and that was the view of the judges who had been closest to the cases from the beginning and the view of the three-judge court generally.", "start": 1754.385, "stop": 1769.349, "duration": 14.96}, {"text": "So how can we reach a result essentially without, you know, re-finding the facts that they have been dealing with for 20 years?", "start": 1769.349, "stop": 1778.16, "duration": 8.81}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "The fundamental problem with the fact-finding in this -- well, there are actually two fundamental problems.", "start": 1778.16, "stop": 1782.349, "duration": 4.19}, {"text": "First of all, remember that the receiver gets appointed and then three months later you get a motion for a three-judge court.", "start": 1782.349, "stop": 1788.832, "duration": 6.48}, {"text": "The three-judge court convenes itself before the receiver has even finalized the comprehensive plan to bring everybody into compliance in the first instance.", "start": 1788.832, "stop": 1797.377, "duration": 8.54}, {"text": "So the reality is that is the fundamental legal error I'm asking this Court to correct.", "start": 1797.377, "stop": 1802.082, "duration": 4.71}, {"text": "But even if you get beyond that and you are looking at the primary cause analysis, it seems to me that's -- that's at most, at best, a mixed question of law and fact, and it's the kind of standard that this Court ought to analyze to determine in the first instance and on an independent review whether or not the overcrowding is \"the primary cause of the violation.\"", "start": 1802.082, "stop": 1821.514, "duration": 19.43}, {"text": "And what makes that inquiry particularly appropriate for this Court, as opposed to simply slavishly adhering and deferring to the district court in this circumstance, is that the district court arbitrarily cut off the record in August of 2008 and there have been enormous developments since then and there were enormous developments --", "start": 1821.514, "stop": 1836.963, "duration": 15.45}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can you explain me something about that, it was confusing in the brief, Mr. Phillips?", "start": 1836.963, "stop": 1841.547, "duration": 4.58}, {"text": "I thought that the State had said, “We don't want the plaintiffs to tour these facilities any more.", "start": 1841.547, "stop": 1853.14, "duration": 11.59}, {"text": "We don't want to have discovery go beyond, what it was, some date in 2008.”", "start": 1853.14, "stop": 1861.013, "duration": 7.87}, {"text": "I thought that it was the State that was urging, “We don't need any more discovery, we don't want any more inspection tours.”", "start": 1861.013, "stop": 1870.979, "duration": 9.97}, {"text": "So how could -- how could the plaintiffs submit more than they did when the State said it's enough, 2008 should be the cutoff?", "start": 1870.979, "stop": 1884.206, "duration": 13.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there is a huge difference between not allowing formal tours and all of the rigamarole that goes with that, which is what the State specifically objected to, but what the State wanted to do and what the Intervenors on our side in even greater vehemence wanted to do was to bring forward evidence that proved that in the interim period of time there have been, in fact, significant improvements.", "start": 1884.206, "stop": 1906.73, "duration": 22.52}, {"text": "As I sit here today, Justice Kennedy, you said it is conceded that we are in constitutional violation.", "start": 1906.73, "stop": 1912.564, "duration": 5.83}, {"text": "It is conceded that we have been in constitutional violation.", "start": 1912.564, "stop": 1916.687, "duration": 4.12}, {"text": "I don't know whether today we are in violation.", "start": 1916.687, "stop": 1917.826, "duration": 1.14}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "But then don't you have the burden?", "start": 1917.826, "stop": 1919.901, "duration": 2.08}, {"text": "If you concede that you have been in constitutional violation, then it seems to me that you have the burden of showing that is no longer the case.", "start": 1919.901, "stop": 1930.731, "duration": 10.83}, {"text": "That's generally so in the --", "start": 1930.731, "stop": 1936.277, "duration": 5.55}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, did you--", "start": 1936.277, "stop": 1938.137, "duration": 1.86}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry.", "start": 1938.137, "stop": 1938.707, "duration": 0.57}, {"text": "Could you answer Justice Ginsburg's question first?", "start": 1938.707, "stop": 1941.308, "duration": 2.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1941.308, "stop": 1941.463, "duration": 0.15}, {"text": "Justice Ginsburg, I understand what the ordinary rule would be of a court of equity dealing with a constitutional violation, but we are talking about an order entered under the Prisoners Litigation Reform Act, and it's quite clear, the statute couldn't be any plainer, that it shifts the burden significantly onto the plaintiff when you are going to go for a remedy as extreme as insisting that somewhere between potentially 36,000 and 45,000 inmates be released within a two-year period of time.", "start": 1941.463, "stop": 1970.468, "duration": 29.01}, {"text": "Again, if you go back, the receiver has not -- at the time that all of this took place, the receiver had been appointed.", "start": 1970.468, "stop": 1976.848, "duration": 6.38}, {"text": "The receiver had devised a plan.", "start": 1976.848, "stop": 1978.676, "duration": 1.83}, {"text": "The receiver is currently spending an enormous amount of money, $4 billion on healthcare, to get -- to get the system moving in the right direction, with the right attitude, in order to bring ourselves without question into constitutional compliance.", "start": 1978.676, "stop": 1993.213, "duration": 14.54}, {"text": "The truth is we haven't really had an assessment of where we are in the constitutional compliance spectrum.", "start": 1993.213, "stop": 1997.205, "duration": 3.99}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, maybe we are talking about one of the cases, but the other one, and it's the newer one in 2000 -- instituted in 2001, but what about the one that started out in 1990?", "start": 1997.205, "stop": 2009.406, "duration": 12.2}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Coleman is obviously a much -- a much more serious problem, I don't doubt that, but it seems -- and if the Court were to conclude ultimately that Coleman ought to go back for another analysis based on the problems there, I could understand that and it would be a very different prisoner release order under those circumstances because then you would have to take out all of the evidence with respect to Plata and let that play out.", "start": 2009.406, "stop": 2033.047, "duration": 23.64}, {"text": "But even that it seems to me would be a mistake under these circumstances where the special master and receiver have been in a sense joined at the hip in a variety of ways, it only makes sense, because the receiver is controlling the provision of medical care in the CDCR and the special master is taking care of or trying to promote a very small slice of that.", "start": 2033.047, "stop": 2055.489, "duration": 22.44}, {"text": "So in the scheme of things, as you might expect, the receiver consistently gets the ultimate authority to make the decisions to help provide the kind of resources, both in quality and quantity and staff and construction and access to healthcare.", "start": 2055.489, "stop": 2070.012, "duration": 14.52}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, this issue about evidence, did you proffer to the judge anywhere in this record what the additional evidence it was that you wanted to show?", "start": 2070.012, "stop": 2082.474, "duration": 12.46}, {"text": "I know that the decrease in suicides happened post-trial, so you couldn't have proffered that pretrial.", "start": 2082.474, "stop": 2091.072, "duration": 8.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2091.072, "stop": 2093.018, "duration": 1.95}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you are from the prisons.", "start": 2093.018, "stop": 2094.728, "duration": 1.71}, {"text": "I presume that you could have yourself without discovery set forth or proffer for the court that says, “We had a wait time between diagnosis and treatment that was 60 days, 90 days, 120 days in the past and we have reduced that down now to two weeks or whatever the reality is.", "start": 2094.728, "stop": 2119.348, "duration": 24.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 2119.348, "stop": 2119.523, "duration": 0.18}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why didn't you -- you keep saying we were blocked.", "start": 2119.523, "stop": 2122.217, "duration": 2.69}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because the district court -- because the district court could not have been plainer and when the Intervenor's counsel stood up in the opening statement and said, I want to start talking about the beneficial changes and where the status is today as opposed to where it was way back when, the three-judge court, at least one of the member of the three-judge court said, “We have been as clear as we can be that we are not entertaining any evidence on that point.”", "start": 2122.217, "stop": 2145.758, "duration": 23.54}, {"text": "So the notion of coming forward with a proffer, while technically it might have been, was clearly a futile act and we had already annoyed the judges on our side by even making reference to it.", "start": 2145.758, "stop": 2155.179, "duration": 9.42}, {"text": "So I don't think it's an appropriate response to say that we should have put forward more, because the (Voice Pverlap) --", "start": 2155.179, "stop": 2159.86, "duration": 4.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Except that the district court invited you to proffer that evidence that went to the appropriateness of the remedy, so you didn't have to proffer it.", "start": 2159.86, "stop": 2169.447, "duration": 9.59}, {"text": "It viewed you as saying, we are no longer violating, constitutionally violating the Eighth Amendment.", "start": 2169.447, "stop": 2179.283, "duration": 9.84}, {"text": "Instead it said, “We will take whatever you have to proffer to show that the remedy is inappropriate.”", "start": 2179.283, "stop": 2185.277, "duration": 5.99}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "But Justice Sotomayor, there is, to my mind at least, a complete disconnect by saying, I'm not going to tell you exactly where the constitutional violation is today.", "start": 2185.277, "stop": 2194.582, "duration": 9.3}, {"text": "We are not going to get into that.", "start": 2194.582, "stop": 2195.637, "duration": 1.06}, {"text": "We are just going to assume there is a constitutional violation.", "start": 2195.637, "stop": 2198.275, "duration": 2.64}, {"text": "Now prove to me that the remedy, you know, what remedy will or will not work under those circumstances.", "start": 2198.275, "stop": 2202.677, "duration": 4.4}, {"text": "It seems to me the exact opposite is the way to do it.", "start": 2202.677, "stop": 2205.148, "duration": 2.47}, {"text": "You determine where the constitutional violation is – (Voice Overlap)", "start": 2205.148, "stop": 2207.421, "duration": 2.27}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, I see your time is about to expire.", "start": 2207.421, "stop": 2209.977, "duration": 2.56}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice.", "start": 2209.977, "stop": 2230.349, "duration": 20.37}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Specter.", "start": 2230.349, "stop": 2231.749, "duration": 1.4}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court.", "start": 2231.749, "stop": 2238.844, "duration": 7.1}, {"text": "For 20 years, the overcrowding crisis has caused prisoners suffering from psychosis and life-threatening illnesses to languish in their cells because treatment facilities have no room for them.", "start": 2238.844, "stop": 2250.626, "duration": 11.78}, {"text": "Prisoners are committing suicide at a rate twice the national average and more than two-thirds of those suicides are preventable.", "start": 2250.626, "stop": 2257.552, "duration": 6.93}, {"text": "The absence of--", "start": 2257.552, "stop": 2257.732, "duration": 0.18}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are you talking about current figures or past?", "start": 2257.732, "stop": 2260.491, "duration": 2.76}, {"text": "Tell us the date of the figures?", "start": 2260.491, "stop": 2261.907, "duration": 1.42}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sure.", "start": 2261.907, "stop": 2262.301, "duration": 0.39}, {"text": "That's from the trial court's opinion, Your Honor.", "start": 2262.301, "stop": 2264.273, "duration": 1.97}, {"text": "That's from the record.", "start": 2264.273, "stop": 2264.895, "duration": 0.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's what I thought.", "start": 2264.895, "stop": 2265.933, "duration": 1.04}, {"text": "How do you address your adversary's point that the adequacy of a remedy can't be measured unless you measure the state of the situation at the time the remedy is imposed?", "start": 2265.933, "stop": 2280.178, "duration": 14.24}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think, Your Honor, there was massive amounts of evidence about the constitutional violations that existed at the time that the remedy was imposed.", "start": 2280.178, "stop": 2291.538, "duration": 11.36}, {"text": "And if we -- I can point to the jurisdictional statement 1 appendix, page 30a, the court said, \"Nonetheless, as we described below, fundamental unconstitutional deficiency is caused primarily by overcrowding continue to exist.\"", "start": 2291.538, "stop": 2309.978, "duration": 18.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "They didn't take any evidence on the point, I thought.", "start": 2309.978, "stop": 2312.448, "duration": 2.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor I'm sorry, that's not correct, with all respect.", "start": 2312.448, "stop": 2315.755, "duration": 3.31}, {"text": "They took massive amounts of evidence up to the day of trial about all the conditions as they relate to the remedy and those conditions were--", "start": 2315.755, "stop": 2324.944, "duration": 9.19}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Could you give us the record?", "start": 2324.944, "stop": 2326.287, "duration": 1.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Current conditions?", "start": 2326.287, "stop": 2327.758, "duration": 1.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Current as of the time of the trial.", "start": 2327.758, "stop": 2328.602, "duration": 0.84}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was -- what was your friend talking about when he said that they rejected any effort to show the current situation?", "start": 2328.602, "stop": 2337.805, "duration": 9.2}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, my friend and I have a disagreement, but I think Justice Sotomayor accurately captured it.", "start": 2337.805, "stop": 2344.777, "duration": 6.97}, {"text": "What the three-judge panel said is, look, we're not going to -- you can't -- this isn't the place for you to come in and say everything's fine, everything's constitutional.", "start": 2344.777, "stop": 2358.348, "duration": 13.57}, {"text": "What the three-judge court did say is, “We will consider” and they did in fact consider all of the evidence from the State, they had experts from the State, two of the prisons, in August 2008, those experts wrote reports, they testified, and they testified about the conditions current and one of them from the mental health --", "start": 2358.348, "stop": 2376.037, "duration": 17.69}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was in 2008.", "start": 2376.037, "stop": 2378.334, "duration": 2.3}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was the time of the trial, Your Honor.", "start": 2378.334, "stop": 2381.199, "duration": 2.87}, {"text": "The discovery--", "start": 2381.199, "stop": 2381.327, "duration": 0.13}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "They had a cutoff date of some two months before the trial.", "start": 2381.327, "stop": 2386.786, "duration": 5.46}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "In August, and the trial started in November.", "start": 2386.786, "stop": 2388.519, "duration": 1.73}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that -- but before that point, the experts that were -- had testified were aware of the conditions that existed?", "start": 2388.519, "stop": 2397.959, "duration": 9.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Exactly, Your Honor.", "start": 2397.959, "stop": 2399.168, "duration": 1.21}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "And when was the remedy imposed?", "start": 2399.168, "stop": 2401.274, "duration": 2.11}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "The remedy -- well, the final order came -- well, the close of evidence was in December of 2008.", "start": 2401.274, "stop": 2407.348, "duration": 6.07}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "That was in the -- in the one-judge court, in the district court, wasn't it?", "start": 2407.348, "stop": 2410.081, "duration": 2.73}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no in the three-judge court.", "start": 2410.081, "stop": 2412.001, "duration": 1.92}, {"text": "The three-judge court closed evidence in December of 2008.", "start": 2412.001, "stop": 2416.394, "duration": 4.39}, {"text": "We then argued the case after the post-trial briefing in February of 2009.", "start": 2416.394, "stop": 2421.579, "duration": 5.19}, {"text": "Then the court came out with the tentative decision about 20 days later, and then in August of 2009, it issued the 183-page opinion and the order.", "start": 2421.579, "stop": 2434.175, "duration": 12.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Didn't you –", "start": 2434.175, "stop": 2434.74, "duration": 0.56}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry, let me just keep track here.", "start": 2434.74, "stop": 2437.075, "duration": 2.34}, {"text": "The evidence was cut off when, in 2008?", "start": 2437.075, "stop": 2440.207, "duration": 3.13}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "The trial closed in December of 2008, after all the parties had submitted all their evidence.", "start": 2440.207, "stop": 2447.397, "duration": 7.19}, {"text": "Then there was post-trial briefing for a month.", "start": 2447.397, "stop": 2451.346, "duration": 3.95}, {"text": "Then we had argument in February of that year and then a few weeks later, they issued a brief summary of their conclusions in an attempt to get the State and the parties to settle the case.", "start": 2451.346, "stop": 2463.061, "duration": 11.72}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "You don't dispute the statement I have, it's in the response to the Intervenors that between October 2006 and October 2010 the population of the adult facilities declined by 14,832 inmates?", "start": 2463.061, "stop": 2480.277, "duration": 17.22}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree with my friend Mr. Phillips that the population has declined by about 10,000 prisoners.", "start": 2480.277, "stop": 2487.504, "duration": 7.23}, {"text": "Most of that decline has been due to transfer to out-of-State prisons, and true, there is some amount of it has been as a result of the marginal increase in good time credits, which the State elected to pursue on its own.", "start": 2487.504, "stop": 2505.642, "duration": 18.14}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "What about the argument that there was evidence that should have been admitted, but that was not with reference to new construction?", "start": 2505.642, "stop": 2513.036, "duration": 7.39}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I don't -- there was no evidence that wasn't -- that was offered that wasn't considered by the three-judge panel, Your Honor.", "start": 2513.036, "stop": 2520.756, "duration": 7.72}, {"text": "They considered all the evidence.", "start": 2520.756, "stop": 2523.007, "duration": 2.25}, {"text": "Their 183-page opinion is scrupulous in considering all the evidence, both that supported the order and they distinguished the evidence and, in fact, made credibility determinations based on the evidence that was contrary.", "start": 2523.007, "stop": 2537.219, "duration": 14.21}, {"text": "But I –", "start": 2537.219, "stop": 2537.468, "duration": 0.25}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Could --", "start": 2537.468, "stop": 2539.287, "duration": 1.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can you explain what the connection is between the 137.5 percent figure and the constitutional violations relating to the provision of medical care in general and treatment for -- for mental illness?", "start": 2539.287, "stop": 2554.962, "duration": 15.68}, {"text": "My understanding of the 137.5 percent figure is that that has to do with the total number of prisoners in the -- in the system in relation to designed capacity, isn't that right?", "start": 2554.962, "stop": 2569.113, "duration": 14.15}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, Your Honor.", "start": 2569.113, "stop": 2570.126, "duration": 1.01}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now, what does the ruling -- that doesn't speak to the number of personnel who are available in the system to attend to medical needs or mental illness?", "start": 2570.126, "stop": 2582.78, "duration": 12.65}, {"text": "It doesn't speak to the extent of the facilities that are available for those purposes.", "start": 2582.78, "stop": 2589.617, "duration": 6.84}, {"text": "It seems to be -- there seems to be a disconnect between those two.", "start": 2589.617, "stop": 2593.057, "duration": 3.44}, {"text": "Could you explain why that is narrowly tailored?", "start": 2593.057, "stop": 2596.527, "duration": 3.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 2596.527, "stop": 2598.461, "duration": 1.93}, {"text": "There was -- the court made findings that 137.5 percent was the maximum number of prisoners that -- of the capacity, of the designed capacity of the prison, that the prison could have that would enable the State to -- to have all those things you just mentioned, staffing, facilities, medication management, be effective and reach the actual prisoners who are ill, seriously ill.", "start": 2598.461, "stop": 2626.805, "duration": 28.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "See, that's what I don't understand.", "start": 2626.805, "stop": 2628.034, "duration": 1.23}, {"text": "You can have a -- could you not have a prison where the cells are somewhat crowded and 137.5 percent of designed capacity is not -- is not unconstitutional in itself, is it?", "start": 2628.034, "stop": 2641.401, "duration": 13.37}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, it -- you could have -- it's a remedy, Your Honor.", "start": 2641.401, "stop": 2644.486, "duration": 3.09}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "You could have a prison where the -- the cells themselves are crowded, and yet there are other facilities available for medical care and plenty of staff to attend to those things.", "start": 2644.486, "stop": 2658.095, "duration": 13.61}, {"text": "So what's the connection?", "start": 2658.095, "stop": 2659.21, "duration": 1.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that's -- that's -- and you're right.", "start": 2659.21, "stop": 2661.581, "duration": 2.37}, {"text": "If there were -- if the cells were crowded, but the prison had all the other facilities available, then there might not be a problem.", "start": 2661.581, "stop": 2669.632, "duration": 8.05}, {"text": "You have to -- well, I hope you can understand that in this case, the prisons were built to double-cell the prisoners, but they weren't built to provide 200 percent of healthcare needs.", "start": 2669.632, "stop": 2682.343, "duration": 12.71}, {"text": "So as soon as they started to double-cell these prisoners, they could meet their literal housing needs in the space of the cell, but they couldn't meet the needs of their healthcare and that's why, Your Honor, the 137.5 percent figure is reasonable because the Court went almost a third overcrowding above what all the experts recommended.", "start": 2682.343, "stop": 2705.781, "duration": 23.44}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "But why order the release of around 40,000 prisoners, many of whom, perhaps the great majority of whom, are not going to be within the class in either of these lawsuits?", "start": 2705.781, "stop": 2719.11, "duration": 13.33}, {"text": "Why order the release of all those people, rather than ordering the provision of the construction of facilities for medical care, facilities to treat mental illness, hiring of staff to treat mental illness?", "start": 2719.11, "stop": 2732.277, "duration": 13.17}, {"text": "Why not go directly to the problem rather than address what seems to be a different issue altogether?", "start": 2732.277, "stop": 2738.989, "duration": 6.71}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I have two responses to that, and they are both a little separate.", "start": 2738.989, "stop": 2743.097, "duration": 4.11}, {"text": "The first point, it's important to understand that this is not a release order.", "start": 2743.097, "stop": 2748.02, "duration": 4.92}, {"text": "It's a population crowding reduction order.", "start": 2748.02, "stop": 2750.816, "duration": 2.8}, {"text": "The court is not ordering the State to throw open the gates of its doors and release people.", "start": 2750.816, "stop": 2755.666, "duration": 4.85}, {"text": "They can reduce crowding through more transfers to out of State.", "start": 2755.666, "stop": 2759.436, "duration": 3.77}, {"text": "To your construction point, if the State still chooses, it can construct new facilities to increase the capacity, and the three-judge panel said if you increase the capacity, you can increase the population.", "start": 2759.436, "stop": 2773.38, "duration": 13.94}, {"text": "The point about--", "start": 2773.38, "stop": 2774.021, "duration": 0.64}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "If all they do is to build more cells, they are not going to address the problem.", "start": 2774.021, "stop": 2777.597, "duration": 3.58}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Exactly.", "start": 2777.597, "stop": 2778.156, "duration": 0.56}, {"text": "So that goes to the second part of your question, which is why don't they try other things, like ordering the prisons to hire more doctors, ordering better medication management, all of those kinds of things?", "start": 2778.156, "stop": 2788.645, "duration": 10.49}, {"text": "And the answer to that is in the appendix to the Appellee's Coleman brief, which lists 70 discrete orders which the Coleman court, single-judge Coleman court, tried over a period of 15 years, which have proven singularly to be ineffective and that is why the court analyzed all those things.", "start": 2788.645, "stop": 2809.305, "duration": 20.66}, {"text": "The trial court analyzed all those things, and it made a finding of fact that based on the statements by the special master, by the receiver's reports, and by the general horrendous conditions which we have in these prisons, that those discrete orders would not solve the problem and given the level of harm --", "start": 2809.305, "stop": 2827.265, "duration": 17.96}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I still don't get it.", "start": 2827.265, "stop": 2828.156, "duration": 0.89}, {"text": "You're saying that they were ordered to do a variety of things that directly addressed the problem and they didn't comply.", "start": 2828.156, "stop": 2833.5, "duration": 5.34}, {"text": "So as a --", "start": 2833.5, "stop": 2834.452, "duration": 0.95}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 2834.452, "stop": 2834.774, "duration": 0.32}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "In order to -- in order to provide some kind of remedy we are going to order something else that doesn't address the problems that these lawsuits aim at addressing.", "start": 2834.774, "stop": 2845.181, "duration": 10.41}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, that -- no, Your Honor, to the contrary, Justice Alito, we -- I think the court believes based on the facts that it found that this would be an effective remedy.", "start": 2845.181, "stop": 2854.88, "duration": 9.7}, {"text": "All of the testimony that they heard from experts from Texas, from Pennsylvania, from Washington State, all of whom had suffered, had dealt with crowding in their prison systems, has said that when you reduce the crowding, that's the critical thing that you have to do now because unless you reduce the crowding, nothing else is going to work, and the court found that that was exactly true.", "start": 2854.88, "stop": 2877.893, "duration": 23.01}, {"text": "Nothing else over 20 years in one case, and over 8 years in another case has worked and all -- as Justice Kennedy said, massive amounts of evidence show that the primary reason it hasn't worked is one singular word, overcrowding and when you reduce overcrowding the prison will be able to operate and will be able to provide those services that it can't provide now, so the doctors will have room to be able to work, which they don't have now.", "start": 2877.893, "stop": 2906.696, "duration": 28.8}, {"text": "There will be less prisoners, so officers will be able to take them from one place to another to get treatment.", "start": 2906.696, "stop": 2913.378, "duration": 6.68}, {"text": "There won't be so many lockdowns which inhibit care.", "start": 2913.378, "stop": 2916.988, "duration": 3.61}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel --", "start": 2916.988, "stop": 2917.325, "duration": 0.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is a very indirect way of addressing the problem and it has collateral consequences.", "start": 2917.325, "stop": 2923.623, "duration": 6.3}, {"text": "If -- if I were a citizen of California, I would be concerned about the release of 40,000 prisoners and I don't care what you term it, a prison release order or whatever the --", "start": 2923.623, "stop": 2936.308, "duration": 12.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Crowding –", "start": 2936.308, "stop": 2936.514, "duration": 0.21}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- terminology you used was.", "start": 2936.514, "stop": 2938.269, "duration": 1.75}, {"text": "If 40,000 prisoners are going to be released, you really believe that if you were to come back here two years after that, you would be able to say, they haven't -- they haven't contributed to an increase in crime --", "start": 2938.269, "stop": 2952.868, "duration": 14.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well --", "start": 2952.868, "stop": 2952.991, "duration": 0.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- in the State of California?", "start": 2952.991, "stop": 2954.025, "duration": 1.03}, {"text": "In the -- in the amicus brief that was submitted by a number of states, there is an extended discussion of the effect of one prisoner release order with which I am familiar, and that was in Philadelphia and after a period of time they tallied up what the cost of that was, the number of murders, the number of rapes, the number of armed robberies, the number of assaults -- you don't -- that's not going to happen in California?", "start": 2954.025, "stop": 2980.734, "duration": 26.71}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, this trial court found based on, 50 pages of its opinion, based on expert testimony, not only from our experts, but from the State's experts, from the Intervenors' experts.", "start": 2980.734, "stop": 2994.532, "duration": 13.8}, {"text": "They all came to the unanimous conclusion that there are methods that -- by which you can reduce crowding which will not increase crime and they are safe.", "start": 2994.532, "stop": 3003.801, "duration": 9.27}, {"text": "The Secretary of the Department of Corrections who was the secretary at the time of trial testified that he was in favor, for example, of increasing prisoner's good time credits.", "start": 3003.801, "stop": 3014.363, "duration": 10.56}, {"text": "That's one way to reduce crowding and moreover, there was statistical evidence saying, looking at all the other States that had reduced their prison population over a period of about 15 years, and they all came to the same conclusion, all of those studies came to the same conclusion, which is there is no -- there is no increase in the crime rate.", "start": 3014.363, "stop": 3037.485, "duration": 23.12}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that is not what -- that is not what the three-judge district court determined.", "start": 3037.485, "stop": 3043.379, "duration": 5.89}, {"text": "The Prisoner Litigation Reform Act requires that court to give substantial weight to adverse impact on public safety.", "start": 3043.379, "stop": 3051.192, "duration": 7.81}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3051.192, "stop": 3051.664, "duration": 0.47}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "And when -- and then it said to the State, look, you come up with a plan that gets you to 137.5 in two years.", "start": 3051.664, "stop": 3058.285, "duration": 6.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3058.285, "stop": 3058.819, "duration": 0.53}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "The State did, and the State did not say, emphatically did not say this is not going to have an adverse impact on public safety.", "start": 3058.819, "stop": 3067.618, "duration": 8.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, but the--", "start": 3067.618, "stop": 3068.198, "duration": 0.58}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is a problem with negative there, but -- and what the district court said, it didn't examine that.", "start": 3068.198, "stop": 3074.078, "duration": 5.88}, {"text": "It said, well, we're sure the state's not going to do anything that has an adverse impact on public safety.", "start": 3074.078, "stop": 3079.326, "duration": 5.25}, {"text": "I am looking at page 4a of the jurisdictional statement.", "start": 3079.326, "stop": 3082.818, "duration": 3.49}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3082.818, "stop": 3083.224, "duration": 0.41}, {"text": "I know --", "start": 3083.224, "stop": 3083.462, "duration": 0.24}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "And said -- and so it did not make those determinations, but the PLRA requires it to determine that what it's ordering or at least gives substantial weight to the public safety issue.", "start": 3083.462, "stop": 3094.625, "duration": 11.16}, {"text": "So isn't that a basis for overturning the remedy that's imposed here?", "start": 3094.625, "stop": 3100.877, "duration": 6.25}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would respectfully disagree with that and I'll tell you why--", "start": 3100.877, "stop": 3103.188, "duration": 2.31}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I thought you would.[Laughter]", "start": 3103.188, "stop": 3106.068, "duration": 2.88}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "At least it's respectful. [Laughter]", "start": 3106.068, "stop": 3110.623, "duration": 4.55}, {"text": "I will tell you why I think that.", "start": 3110.623, "stop": 3113.238, "duration": 2.61}, {"text": "The court examined all of the methods that are commonly used and that the governor himself has proposed to reduce crowding.", "start": 3113.238, "stop": 3125.043, "duration": 11.81}, {"text": "The governor himself wanted to reduce the prison population by 37,000.", "start": 3125.043, "stop": 3129.918, "duration": 4.88}, {"text": "That was in one of his legislative enactments, and the Secretary of Corrections testified that those proposals were safe.", "start": 3129.918, "stop": 3136.578, "duration": 6.66}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Did he want to do it within the two-year period the district court ordered?", "start": 3136.578, "stop": 3139.667, "duration": 3.09}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, he did.", "start": 3139.667, "stop": 3141.038, "duration": 1.37}, {"text": "He submitted legislation to the legislature for that, and the legislature wouldn't -- wouldn't take it and the governor actually said, reacting to that, after a riot at Chino which was partly -- at one of the -- Chino is a prison in California, a riot, he said, \"And the politicians in Sacramento have swept the problem under the rug.\"", "start": 3141.038, "stop": 3163.61, "duration": 22.57}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right, right.", "start": 3163.61, "stop": 3164.182, "duration": 0.57}, {"text": "Now my -- my question is specifically with respect to the --", "start": 3164.182, "stop": 3166.934, "duration": 2.75}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'll get to that.", "start": 3166.934, "stop": 3167.397, "duration": 0.46}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- with respect to the two-year plan --", "start": 3167.397, "stop": 3168.364, "duration": 0.97}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3168.364, "stop": 3168.862, "duration": 0.5}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and I would like an answer to that.", "start": 3168.862, "stop": 3170.212, "duration": 1.35}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3170.212, "stop": 3170.36, "duration": 0.15}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "As I look at this record, I see that the district court did what was required by the Act with respect to the plan that it's ordering.", "start": 3170.36, "stop": 3177.905, "duration": 7.55}, {"text": "It just simply said, oh, we're sure -- I'm the State wouldn't do anything to hurt public safety, after telling the State you have got to give me a plan in two years that gets to 137.5.", "start": 3177.905, "stop": 3187.804, "duration": 9.9}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3187.804, "stop": 3188.345, "duration": 0.54}, {"text": "Well, I think all of the -- it didn't -- it didn't analyze the plan, because the court was trying -- well, there was no plan.", "start": 3188.345, "stop": 3197.22, "duration": 8.88}, {"text": "The court, what they -- what the court did was it said, we want to give the State the maximum flexibility for comity reasons to determine how best to remedy the constitutional violations.", "start": 3197.22, "stop": 3211.186, "duration": 13.97}, {"text": "Now I am certain then they said -- they also said that we're sure the State can do it in a safe way, but it's not our job to -- the method.", "start": 3211.186, "stop": 3218.948, "duration": 7.76}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, they said we're sure, because we trust, I'm just quoting from 4a, \"We trust that the State will comply with its duty to ensure public safety as it implements the constitutionally required reduction.\"", "start": 3218.948, "stop": 3231.43, "duration": 12.48}, {"text": "The State is saying it cannot meet the 137.5 in two years without an adverse impact on public safety.", "start": 3231.43, "stop": 3237.226, "duration": 5.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right and the -- that's the State's position and had been the State's position all along.", "start": 3237.226, "stop": 3242.027, "duration": 4.8}, {"text": "The court's findings that a population reduction of this magnitude were clear and they are not shown to be clearly erroneous here.", "start": 3242.027, "stop": 3249.879, "duration": 7.85}, {"text": "They -- the court said point blank that we -- we're -- it's our finding that the State can reduce the population to its current levels -- from its current levels to 137.5 safely.", "start": 3249.879, "stop": 3265.845, "duration": 15.97}, {"text": "They made that finding--", "start": 3265.845, "stop": 3266.245, "duration": 0.4}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, didn't the court --", "start": 3266.245, "stop": 3267.289, "duration": 1.04}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and they haven't been shown to be clearly erroneous.", "start": 3267.289, "stop": 3269.419, "duration": 2.13}, {"text": "So they didn't have to look at particulars.", "start": 3269.419, "stop": 3273.116, "duration": 3.7}, {"text": "In an effort to give the State the maximum flexibility, they wanted to allow the State to choose the methods that it wanted.", "start": 3273.116, "stop": 3280.359, "duration": 7.24}, {"text": "If the State -- if the court had ordered--", "start": 3280.359, "stop": 3282.163, "duration": 1.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel --", "start": 3282.163, "stop": 3282.464, "duration": 0.3}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what do you mean they can do it?", "start": 3282.464, "stop": 3283.266, "duration": 0.8}, {"text": "Of course they could do it safely if they built, you know, umpteen new prisons, but that's --", "start": 3283.266, "stop": 3287.846, "duration": 4.58}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "But they can also do it safely --", "start": 3287.846, "stop": 3289.216, "duration": 1.37}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "You know, that's pie in the sky, that's not going to happen.", "start": 3289.216, "stop": 3290.605, "duration": 1.39}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, it isn't, Your Honor, because they can also do it safely by good time credits.", "start": 3290.605, "stop": 3294.12, "duration": 3.51}, {"text": "They can do it safely --", "start": 3294.12, "stop": 3295.595, "duration": 1.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Antonin Scalia", "textObjs": [{"text": "Doesn't good time credits let -- let people out who would not otherwise be out?", "start": 3295.595, "stop": 3299.843, "duration": 4.25}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Just a -- you know, the evidence was at trial, and the court's finding about that evidence was, and the State officials so testified, that giving prisoners good time credits is not a threat to public safety.", "start": 3299.843, "stop": 3316.123, "duration": 16.28}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel.", "start": 3316.123, "stop": 3316.504, "duration": 0.38}, {"text": "Didn't –", "start": 3316.504, "stop": 3317.321, "duration": 0.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why wouldn't it have been the better course, for the State -- for the court to say, you know, the State said it can do this in five years without any public safety problem?", "start": 3317.321, "stop": 3327.498, "duration": 10.18}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3327.498, "stop": 3328.321, "duration": 0.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "So why don't we let them take those five years?", "start": 3328.321, "stop": 3332.124, "duration": 3.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because Your Honor as Justice Ginsburg and others have been saying before the constitutional violations have been ongoing for 20 years.", "start": 3332.124, "stop": 3340.879, "duration": 8.76}, {"text": "We are dealing here with cases of life and death and serious injury.", "start": 3340.879, "stop": 3345.631, "duration": 4.75}, {"text": "And after all these years, when they -- when they heard the evidence that said that population could be -- and they made the findings which the State doesn't argue were clearly erroneous, and they made those findings that it could be reduced safely, they had an obligation to provide a remedy that would provide constitutionally adequate care in the safest manner possible -- in the quickest manner possible.", "start": 3345.631, "stop": 3370.359, "duration": 24.73}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think --", "start": 3370.359, "stop": 3370.896, "duration": 0.54}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel--", "start": 3370.896, "stop": 3371.733, "duration": 0.84}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think Justice Sotomayor has been patient.", "start": 3371.733, "stop": 3374.139, "duration": 2.41}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "I have several questions but I'm not sure why -- you have not been responding to Justice -- to the Chief Justice.", "start": 3374.139, "stop": 3384.927, "duration": 10.79}, {"text": "Didn't the district court discuss different safe ways of reducing the population?", "start": 3384.927, "stop": 3391.224, "duration": 6.3}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3391.224, "stop": 3391.514, "duration": 0.29}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "And said, we are not imposing them because we want the State to do -- to choose among them?", "start": 3391.514, "stop": 3396.175, "duration": 4.66}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3396.175, "stop": 3397.022, "duration": 0.85}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "As I've looked at the State's final plan, I thought that they had in fact not only accepted all of the recommendations, but they added a couple of additional remedies that the court had not suggested?", "start": 3397.022, "stop": 3412.94, "duration": 15.92}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3412.94, "stop": 3413.587, "duration": 0.65}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is it a fair statement that the district, that the three judge panel was saying, if you do these things that's their finding, you can do it without affecting public safety, wasn't that what they were saying?", "start": 3413.587, "stop": 3424.992, "duration": 11.41}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, if I didn't make that clear, I meant to.", "start": 3424.992, "stop": 3427.352, "duration": 2.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The second more important question was going back to something that Justice Scalia asked you, which was, you made the statement that no one was stopped from proffering evidence about prison conditions up till two months before the trial.", "start": 3427.352, "stop": 3444.097, "duration": 16.75}, {"text": "So what evidence was excluded?", "start": 3444.097, "stop": 3447.936, "duration": 3.84}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Nothing.", "start": 3447.936, "stop": 3449.052, "duration": 1.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "What point is the other side making that they were excluded from making?", "start": 3449.052, "stop": 3455.649, "duration": 6.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, as we said in our briefs, Your Honor, there was no evidence that was excluded, and in fact, the State's witnesses testified about conditions, some of the conditions current as of the day of the testimony.", "start": 3455.649, "stop": 3470.316, "duration": 14.67}, {"text": "So it was very current.", "start": 3470.316, "stop": 3471.163, "duration": 0.85}, {"text": "Nothing was excluded.", "start": 3471.163, "stop": 3472.341, "duration": 1.18}, {"text": "Even if the Court made a ruling which was error, which we don't believe it was, there was absolutely no prejudice.", "start": 3472.341, "stop": 3479.236, "duration": 6.89}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "What is the number?", "start": 3479.236, "stop": 3481.077, "duration": 1.84}, {"text": "I was puzzled about the same thing that Justice Sotomayor was.", "start": 3481.077, "stop": 3485.401, "duration": 4.32}, {"text": "I read on page 253 of the appendix a conclusion where the district court said it is our conclusion that they can reduce this by how many people, what is it, 30,000 -- it's a lot?", "start": 3485.401, "stop": 3497.538, "duration": 12.14}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "35,000.", "start": 3497.538, "stop": 3498.355, "duration": 0.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "35,000, and this could be done safely.", "start": 3498.355, "stop": 3500.914, "duration": 2.56}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3500.914, "stop": 3501.2, "duration": 0.29}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Preceding page, whatever that was, 253.", "start": 3501.2, "stop": 3505.563, "duration": 4.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 3505.563, "stop": 3505.813, "duration": 0.25}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "There are about six pages where they summarize evidence from all kinds of criminologists that say, for example, there are 17,000 technical parole violators that are being sent to prison who haven't committed additional crimes and they could perhaps be released from some of the time that they're spending in prison.", "start": 3505.813, "stop": 3525.311, "duration": 19.5}, {"text": "Then they go on to this good time, which would, I guess, lead to people who are 50 years old or 60 years old who have been in prison for 40 years would be released at age 55 instead of age 75, I guess there is some category there.", "start": 3525.311, "stop": 3538.783, "duration": 13.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3538.783, "stop": 3539.183, "duration": 0.4}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then they had several other things.", "start": 3539.183, "stop": 3541.303, "duration": 2.12}, {"text": "Okay, now what are some facts about that?", "start": 3541.303, "stop": 3544.627, "duration": 3.32}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "And there was also testimony that the Department Of Corrections was using a risk assessment instrument to identify the low risk prisoners.", "start": 3544.627, "stop": 3553.716, "duration": 9.09}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Isn't it true that in one of the main programs that was cited as providing a safeguard is evidence-based rehabilitation programs?", "start": 3553.716, "stop": 3563.988, "duration": 10.27}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3563.988, "stop": 3564.811, "duration": 0.82}, {"text": "All the witnesses from the State, the Interveners, the local witnesses, our experts, they all found that those would help reduce crime and that they would be most effective if they were continued, but they would be effective also if they were --", "start": 3564.811, "stop": 3579.636, "duration": 14.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What is the general record on the success of rehabilitation efforts?", "start": 3579.636, "stop": 3583.312, "duration": 3.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, you can't say generally because different programs have different records.", "start": 3583.312, "stop": 3588.322, "duration": 5.01}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What did Congress think when it enacted the sentencing format?", "start": 3588.322, "stop": 3594.492, "duration": 6.17}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know.", "start": 3594.492, "stop": 3596.869, "duration": 2.38}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I have this question and this goes just to remedy.", "start": 3596.869, "stop": 3602.603, "duration": 5.73}, {"text": "I recognize that district court has to be given considerable discretion.", "start": 3602.603, "stop": 3607.429, "duration": 4.83}, {"text": "It shows the 137.5 figure because it is halfway between 145 and 130.", "start": 3607.429, "stop": 3612.195, "duration": 4.77}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3612.195, "stop": 3614.022, "duration": 1.83}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think that certainly the Prison Litigation Reform Act means that you have to, if there is going to be a release order, it must be releasing the minimum amount.", "start": 3614.022, "stop": 3624.468, "duration": 10.45}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3624.468, "stop": 3625.267, "duration": 0.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "That will affect the purposes of the remedy order.", "start": 3625.267, "stop": 3629.931, "duration": 4.66}, {"text": "There was substantial expert opinion that 145 -- 145 percent would be sufficient.", "start": 3629.931, "stop": 3639.723, "duration": 9.79}, {"text": "Doesn't the evidence indicate to you that at least 145 ought to be the beginning point, not 137.5?", "start": 3639.723, "stop": 3647.154, "duration": 7.43}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well --", "start": 3647.154, "stop": 3648.389, "duration": 1.24}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And I understand -- may I make -- there were more, correct me if I am wrong, there were more experts that testified that 145 would work then there were that 130 was necessary?", "start": 3648.389, "stop": 3659.893, "duration": 11.5}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 3659.893, "stop": 3662.021, "duration": 2.13}, {"text": "I respectfully disagree with the record, Your Honor.", "start": 3662.021, "stop": 3664.445, "duration": 2.42}, {"text": "The 145 figure came from a report by the former governor, Duke Majin, and a group that he organized and they said that they could operate a crowded system at 145 percent of capacity and that figure was high, the district court found, because it didn't take into account healthcare needs.", "start": 3664.445, "stop": 3686.735, "duration": 22.29}, {"text": "It didn't take into account healthcare needs, which is the issue here and our experts testified that because it didn't take into account healthcare needs, 130 percent was the better number.", "start": 3686.735, "stop": 3699.302, "duration": 12.57}, {"text": "It's the number that the strike team had thought of, the administration's own strike team.", "start": 3699.302, "stop": 3706.153, "duration": 6.85}, {"text": "It's the number that these professional experts believed would be sufficient to remedy the population and back to my answer to Justice Alito's question is, the healthcare facilities themselves were built to provide services to only 100 percent -- healthcare services to only 100 percent of prisoners.", "start": 3706.153, "stop": 3727.983, "duration": 21.83}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "But the experts -- the experts who were testifying were quite aware of the fact that overcrowding related to the constitutional violations, that was their whole theory.", "start": 3727.983, "stop": 3740.058, "duration": 12.07}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3740.058, "stop": 3740.675, "duration": 0.62}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "And any number of them suggested that 145.", "start": 3740.675, "stop": 3743.796, "duration": 3.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think there might have been only one, one expert suggested 145.", "start": 3743.796, "stop": 3749.267, "duration": 5.47}, {"text": "I think most, the majority of the experts suggested 130.", "start": 3749.267, "stop": 3754.017, "duration": 4.75}, {"text": "The court found and it has not been challenged here as clearly erroneous, that the weight of the evidence went to 130.", "start": 3754.017, "stop": 3760.429, "duration": 6.41}, {"text": "They wanted to do what you're saying, which was to minimize the intrusion and maximize the population.", "start": 3760.429, "stop": 3766.388, "duration": 5.96}, {"text": "So even though they found, the Court had ample basis to issue an order saying it should be 130, they said in an abundance of caution and to give the State the benefit of the doubt and to make sure, we are going to bump it up an extra 7.5 percent.", "start": 3766.388, "stop": 3782.025, "duration": 15.64}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see no evidence in the record that the State -- pardon me, that your clients said that 145 wouldn't work.", "start": 3782.025, "stop": 3793.924, "duration": 11.9}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think --", "start": 3793.924, "stop": 3794.983, "duration": 1.06}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Maybe you can answer.", "start": 3794.983, "stop": 3796.096, "duration": 1.11}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Just the experts.", "start": 3796.096, "stop": 3796.928, "duration": 0.83}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Maybe you can answer, counsel, please.", "start": 3796.928, "stop": 3798.895, "duration": 1.97}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you.", "start": 3798.895, "stop": 3801.87, "duration": 2.97}, {"text": "My recollection of the testimony was that our experts said it had to get down to 130 in order for the other remedies to be effective, Your Honor.", "start": 3801.87, "stop": 3811.75, "duration": 9.88}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The expert who gave the 145?", "start": 3811.75, "stop": 3814.268, "duration": 2.52}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Pardon me?", "start": 3814.268, "stop": 3814.897, "duration": 0.63}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "The expert who gave the 145?", "start": 3814.897, "stop": 3816.997, "duration": 2.1}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "There was no expert -- well, there was one expert who said maybe in the best of circumstances it could get to 145.", "start": 3816.997, "stop": 3823.278, "duration": 6.28}, {"text": "All the others talked about 130 percent.", "start": 3823.278, "stop": 3825.871, "duration": 2.59}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Let's go to the one who's used the 145 figure.", "start": 3825.871, "stop": 3828.602, "duration": 2.73}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was a psychologist, Your Honor.", "start": 3828.602, "stop": 3830.829, "duration": 2.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was a what?", "start": 3830.829, "stop": 3831.466, "duration": 0.64}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was a psychologist who has expertise in prison healthcare.", "start": 3831.466, "stop": 3835.703, "duration": 4.24}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "And did he say that 145 you could deliver healthcare?", "start": 3835.703, "stop": 3840.296, "duration": 4.59}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "He was equivocal on that point.", "start": 3840.296, "stop": 3842.11, "duration": 1.81}, {"text": "He thought -- he said that at the outer reaches it might be true, but I want to emphasize that the district court has allowed the State to come back in at any time to modify its order and to modify this percentage point if the circumstances changed.", "start": 3842.11, "stop": 3860.36, "duration": 18.25}, {"text": "So –", "start": 3860.36, "stop": 3860.872, "duration": 0.51}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Specter, there has been at least two significant changes; one is the good time credit.", "start": 3860.872, "stop": 3868.488, "duration": 7.62}, {"text": "The California legislature did pass the law that upped the good time credit, and also addressing the probationers and the parolees, the technical violators from the system.", "start": 3868.488, "stop": 3883.469, "duration": 14.98}, {"text": "Do you have any information about what effect that legislation was passed January?", "start": 3883.469, "stop": 3892.363, "duration": 8.89}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "It was passed, I think, last year and I think it went into effect in July of last year, I believe, if that's what you are referring to.", "start": 3892.363, "stop": 3900.837, "duration": 8.47}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "So do we know at all what effect this has had?", "start": 3900.837, "stop": 3906.222, "duration": 5.39}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "It has had a marginal effect on reducing the population.", "start": 3906.222, "stop": 3909.375, "duration": 3.15}, {"text": "There have been no reports that it has led to an increase in crime, but to get back to my earlier point, and your point, Justice Kennedy, about the remedy and that it should be the least intrusive possible, this order is set to take effect over a two-year period and during that two-year period, if Mr. Phillips is correct that the conditions are constitutional and that they can deliver services at 145 percent, then the State is free to come in and make a motion to bring those changed circumstances to the court and, if anything, this Court has been incredibly sensitive to the needs and desires of the State.", "start": 3909.375, "stop": 3955.635, "duration": 46.26}, {"text": "And it was extremely reluctant to enter this order in the first place and it would bend over backwards to give the State discretion.", "start": 3955.635, "stop": 3964.431, "duration": 8.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't see a finding by the three-judge court that 145, is it, would not be an efficacious remedy.", "start": 3964.431, "stop": 3977.699, "duration": 13.27}, {"text": "I know that it would for 137.", "start": 3977.699, "stop": 3982.622, "duration": 4.92}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3982.622, "stop": 3983.21, "duration": 0.59}, {"text": "I don't think -- I don't think it's explicitly said 145, but I think it discussed the 145 figure in the context of the fact that it didn't provide for healthcare services.", "start": 3983.21, "stop": 3994.701, "duration": 11.49}, {"text": "So it discounted that a little bit and went down about 7 percent, but it came close to that figure, I believe.", "start": 3994.701, "stop": 4001.48, "duration": 6.78}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Can I ask you a hypothetical question that I know is not your case, but let's say you had the district court entering an order saying you have to bring it down to 137.5 in 2 years.", "start": 4001.48, "stop": 4013.808, "duration": 12.33}, {"text": "That will as a practical matter result in the release of 40,000 prisoners.", "start": 4013.808, "stop": 4018.497, "duration": 4.69}, {"text": "The State comes back and makes a showing supported by experts saying, look, if you give us 4 years, we can reach the figure without releasing any prisoners.", "start": 4018.497, "stop": 4027.842, "duration": 9.35}, {"text": "Do you think it would violate the Prison Litigation Reform Act for the district court to say, no, I want this done in 2 years, not 4 years, and we just have to deal with the fact that there are going to be 40,000 prisoners out on the streets?", "start": 4027.842, "stop": 4039.981, "duration": 12.14}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the Prison Litigation Reform Act requires the court to give substantial weight to the public safety implications of its decision.", "start": 4039.981, "stop": 4048.487, "duration": 8.51}, {"text": "So under those circumstances, it's -- under those hypothetical circumstances, there is always the possibility that in those cases, the degree of public safety problems might outweigh the harm.", "start": 4048.487, "stop": 4068.003, "duration": 19.52}, {"text": "That -- as you said, that's not this case.", "start": 4068.003, "stop": 4069.936, "duration": 1.93}, {"text": "They found that we could do it and they -- the three-judge panel found that the State could reduce the population safely.", "start": 4069.936, "stop": 4079.194, "duration": 9.26}, {"text": "And there was no suggestion then in the record that this 2 or 4-year period would make that much of a difference.", "start": 4079.194, "stop": 4085.04, "duration": 5.85}, {"text": "You have to put the 40,000 or 35,000 figure in context.", "start": 4085.04, "stop": 4090.687, "duration": 5.65}, {"text": "California releases 120,000 prisoners every year on parole.", "start": 4090.687, "stop": 4097.102, "duration": 6.41}, {"text": "That's a lot of prisoners and the findings of the district courts are, even when the California increases the number of parolees in the communities, that doesn't increase the crime rate.", "start": 4097.102, "stop": 4107.79, "duration": 10.69}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What is the recidivism rate for those parolees?", "start": 4107.79, "stop": 4111.89, "duration": 4.1}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it depends on the risk of the parolee.", "start": 4111.89, "stop": 4114.72, "duration": 2.83}, {"text": "The high-risk ones --", "start": 4114.72, "stop": 4115.537, "duration": 0.82}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "In general, what is the recidivism rate?", "start": 4115.537, "stop": 4117.502, "duration": 1.97}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, overall, the risk is around 70 percent, but for low-risk prisoners the risk is 17 percent who reviolate.", "start": 4117.502, "stop": 4127.721, "duration": 10.22}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry.", "start": 4127.721, "stop": 4128.022, "duration": 0.3}, {"text": "I couldn't -- what was the first--", "start": 4128.022, "stop": 4130.353, "duration": 2.33}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "The first number when you take all parolees, all together, it's 70 percent.", "start": 4130.353, "stop": 4134.705, "duration": 4.35}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "70?", "start": 4134.705, "stop": 4135.499, "duration": 0.79}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "70, because -- within three years.", "start": 4135.499, "stop": 4138.263, "duration": 2.76}, {"text": "That's what -- the situation we have now, and that's the situation that the governor, the secretary, and the court described as a failure.", "start": 4138.263, "stop": 4146.818, "duration": 8.56}, {"text": "With parole reform, you could reduce that number in many ways, and the court described how you could do that, but the lowest --", "start": 4146.818, "stop": 4154.1, "duration": 7.28}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What is the lowest?", "start": 4154.1, "stop": 4154.673, "duration": 0.57}, {"text": "It's 17 percent.", "start": 4154.673, "stop": 4155.477, "duration": 0.8}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "17 percent and California has a risk assessment instrument which the court found could be used to make sure that what happened in Philadelphia doesn't happen again. (Voice Overlap)", "start": 4155.477, "stop": 4167.256, "duration": 11.78}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I understood that of the low-risk, if only the low-risk people are released, around 3,000 of them are going to commit another crime.", "start": 4167.256, "stop": 4175.376, "duration": 8.12}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "They -- but they don't have to be released, first off I want to make sure I emphasize the point that this is a crowding reduction measure.", "start": 4175.376, "stop": 4182.483, "duration": 7.11}, {"text": "You don't have to release 35,000 prisoners.", "start": 4182.483, "stop": 4185.84, "duration": 3.36}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "They don't have to be released if you can build enough cells --", "start": 4185.84, "stop": 4189.072, "duration": 3.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Or you can divert, or you can improve the parole system so that parole violators don't commit so many crimes, if you offer rehabilitation alternatives, if you provide a number of diversion into the community.", "start": 4189.072, "stop": 4202.756, "duration": 13.68}, {"text": "There are a number of options short of releasing prisoners and the 70 percent figure concludes --", "start": 4202.756, "stop": 4208.096, "duration": 5.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "The 17 percent figure goes exactly to my concern.", "start": 4208.096, "stop": 4213.278, "duration": 5.18}, {"text": "This is going to have -- it seems likely this is going to have an effect on public safety and the experts can testify to whatever they want, but you know what, if this order goes into effect, we will see.", "start": 4213.278, "stop": 4225.592, "duration": 12.31}, {"text": "We will see, and the people of California will see.", "start": 4225.592, "stop": 4228.089, "duration": 2.5}, {"text": "Are there more crimes or are there not?", "start": 4228.089, "stop": 4229.853, "duration": 1.76}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well based on the experience in other jurisdictions, the court found we wouldn't and I wanted to say -- to clarify one point, Your Honor, the 70 percent figure includes -- doesn't always include crimes.", "start": 4229.853, "stop": 4241.134, "duration": 11.28}, {"text": "It includes lots of technical parole violators, people who have missed their appointments, for example.", "start": 4241.134, "stop": 4246.419, "duration": 5.28}, {"text": "So it's not as grave as some of the figures that are informed by the other side.", "start": 4246.419, "stop": 4250.631, "duration": 4.21}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there any –", "start": 4250.631, "stop": 4251.552, "duration": 0.92}]}, {"speakerName": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is -- is there any other case where the prison reduction has been done under the PLRA, or is this the first -- the first one?", "start": 4251.552, "stop": 4262.87, "duration": 11.32}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's the first one to reach this Court, obviously.", "start": 4262.87, "stop": 4264.863, "duration": 1.99}, {"text": "There have been a few others that have been resolved by consent, as I understand it, or not appealed, but just a few.", "start": 4264.863, "stop": 4273.081, "duration": 8.22}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there any evidence on -- I see their suggestions -- the technical parole violators go elsewhere.", "start": 4273.081, "stop": 4283.12, "duration": 10.04}, {"text": "The elderly and infirmed prisoners, some of them be released.", "start": 4283.12, "stop": 4287.876, "duration": 4.76}, {"text": "The good time credits for older people were -- would have effect, be increased, and also, halfway houses and other kinds of prison facilities which used to be called less -- less physically restrictive punishments, or taking the money you save and building new prisons. Okay, that seems to be the gamut.", "start": 4287.876, "stop": 4308.655, "duration": 20.78}, {"text": "Is there any evidence, statistically or otherwise because it used to be that States did rely on halfway houses, it relied upon, they relied upon -- they relied upon certain camps -- prison camps, for example -- and some of them were pretty tough and there were a whole range of what used to be called intermediate punishments.", "start": 4308.655, "stop": 4328.044, "duration": 19.39}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 4328.044, "stop": 4328.808, "duration": 0.76}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right is there any statistical evidence on the part -- on the point that Justice Alito raised --", "start": 4328.808, "stop": 4335.236, "duration": 6.43}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 4335.236, "stop": 4335.972, "duration": 0.74}]}, {"speakerName": "Stephen G. Breyer", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- as to whether these did or did not result in higher crime rates?", "start": 4335.972, "stop": 4338.649, "duration": 2.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the evidence was, and the Court found -- and again, it's not clear error that these programs were more effective than prison in reducing recidivism and they were less expensive and -- and that's part of the reason why the three-judge panel concluded that a reduction in the prison population wouldn't increase crime.", "start": 4338.649, "stop": 4361.954, "duration": 23.3}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, one of the things that concern me about this type of institutional reform litigation is that the State is responsible for a lot of different things.", "start": 4361.954, "stop": 4370.242, "duration": 8.29}, {"text": "What happens when you have this case, another district court ordering the State to take action with respect to environmental damage, another court saying you have got to spend this much more on education for disabled, another court saying you have got to spend this much more on something else?", "start": 4370.242, "stop": 4387.225, "duration": 16.98}, {"text": "How does the State sort out its obligations?", "start": 4387.225, "stop": 4391.024, "duration": 3.8}, {"text": "Does it say, well I'll spend more money to build prisons, but I will violate this other district court order saying I have to spend money to build water treatment plants?", "start": 4391.024, "stop": 4401.124, "duration": 10.1}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well Your Honor, in this particular case --", "start": 4401.124, "stop": 4403.874, "duration": 2.75}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "I know you like your particular case.", "start": 4403.874, "stop": 4405.482, "duration": 1.61}, {"text": "You want the State to say, this is where I'm going to put my money, but the point is that it's a bunch prioritization that the State has to go through every day, and now it's being transferred from the State legislature to Federal district courts throughout the State.", "start": 4405.482, "stop": 4419.617, "duration": 14.14}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I believe the Federal courts have an obligation to enforce the Constitution and the laws.", "start": 4419.617, "stop": 4423.748, "duration": 4.13}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no, I believe that as well, Counsel.", "start": 4423.748, "stop": 4426.132, "duration": 2.38}, {"text": "What I'm saying is that you have conflicting orders from different district courts telling them, you have got to comply with the Constitution by spending 8 billion here and another court saying, I have got another constitutional problem of my own, and you have got to spend 8 billion over there.", "start": 4426.132, "stop": 4441.201, "duration": 15.07}, {"text": "What is the State supposed to do in that situation?", "start": 4441.201, "stop": 4443.749, "duration": 2.55}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, my simple answer to your question, Your Honor, and I don't mean to be flippant, but they're -- they have an obligation to follow the Federal law, the constitutional law, and other laws and if they are not, then the Federal court has an obligation to impose a remedy.", "start": 4443.749, "stop": 4460.339, "duration": 16.59}, {"text": "In this particular case, the State has a choice.", "start": 4460.339, "stop": 4463.846, "duration": 3.51}, {"text": "It can either incarcerate 140,000 prisoners in a system built for 80,000, or it can incarcerate a lesser number.", "start": 4463.846, "stop": 4473.657, "duration": 9.81}, {"text": "If it chooses to incarcerate 148,000 prisoners in a space built for 80, it's going to incur certain obligations and we believe, as I said in the answer to Justice Breyer's question, the State could choose to use less restrictive punishments, alternative punishments, get a better bang for their buck, have more public safety, but that's -- if we -- if the court imposed that kind of a rule, then the State would be here saying it's -- it's violating comity provisions and making policy choices for the State which it shouldn't.", "start": 4473.657, "stop": 4507.023, "duration": 33.37}, {"text": "I believe in this case, the court gave the State the maximum degree of flexibility to make all the policy choices surrounding -- surrounding the incarceration of these prisoners.", "start": 4507.023, "stop": 4516.447, "duration": 9.42}, {"text": "You just -- the Constitution prevents the State from incarcerating somebody and then not providing them the basic medical care they need to escape from the prison and not die before their sentence is out and that's what we have here.", "start": 4516.447, "stop": 4531.487, "duration": 15.04}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 4531.487, "stop": 4531.968, "duration": 0.48}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "If you take the State's concession that it can meet a goal in 5 years and the Federal court order is 2 years, we are talking about 3 years.", "start": 4531.968, "stop": 4545.871, "duration": 13.9}, {"text": "Is there any indication of how fast the State's remedy would click in?", "start": 4545.871, "stop": 4551.364, "duration": 5.49}, {"text": "Are we talking maybe about a 5 percent differential for the last 3 years, or --", "start": 4551.364, "stop": 4556.291, "duration": 4.93}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there are a lot of things the State can do quickly.", "start": 4556.291, "stop": 4559.341, "duration": 3.05}, {"text": "For instance, it can reform its parole system.", "start": 4559.341, "stop": 4561.735, "duration": 2.39}, {"text": "It cannot re-incarcerate technical parole violators.", "start": 4561.735, "stop": 4565.378, "duration": 3.64}, {"text": "It can--", "start": 4565.378, "stop": 4565.607, "duration": 0.23}]}, {"speakerName": "Anthony M. Kennedy", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no.", "start": 4565.607, "stop": 4566.487, "duration": 0.88}, {"text": "I'm saying, assuming -- compare what the State concedes that it will do with what the court has ordered it to do.", "start": 4566.487, "stop": 4574.823, "duration": 8.34}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "--The State -- well, I just want to remind you that the governor proposed to the legislature that he reduced the prison population.", "start": 4574.823, "stop": 4581.855, "duration": 7.03}, {"text": "He said it could be done safely by the same amount, roughly 37,000 prisoners in 2 years.", "start": 4581.855, "stop": 4588.057, "duration": 6.2}, {"text": "So what the court found was basically what the governor had believed was safe.", "start": 4588.057, "stop": 4593.404, "duration": 5.35}, {"text": "The 5-year -- the 5-year period is longer and the 5-year period is longer because it takes time to construct the facilities that the -- that State wants to construct.", "start": 4593.404, "stop": 4604.698, "duration": 11.29}, {"text": "I believe that's the major difference between the two remedies.", "start": 4604.698, "stop": 4608.974, "duration": 4.28}, {"text": "But the other methods, the good time credits, parole reform, diversion, those can be implemented very quickly, and those substantial reductions can be accomplished safely in that amount of time.", "start": 4608.974, "stop": 4621.896, "duration": 12.92}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So should the court have said 2 years for everything but construction? Wouldn't that have been a more narrowly tailored remedy?", "start": 4621.896, "stop": 4633.263, "duration": 11.37}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the State --", "start": 4633.263, "stop": 4633.922, "duration": 0.66}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "Except that they --", "start": 4633.922, "stop": 4634.955, "duration": 1.03}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "I was --", "start": 4634.955, "stop": 4635.126, "duration": 0.17}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- that there was going to be no construction adequate, because there was no money.", "start": 4635.126, "stop": 4638.81, "duration": 3.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Donald Specter", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right and the State has -- has really not put up the money to construct those new prisons.", "start": 4638.81, "stop": 4644.577, "duration": 5.77}, {"text": "This case has been on going since 2006 and they have hardly constructed anything.", "start": 4644.577, "stop": 4649.643, "duration": 5.07}, {"text": "Even if it was a more narrow remedy, the court found that construction wouldn't be a viable alternative.", "start": 4649.643, "stop": 4655.665, "duration": 6.02}, {"text": "My time is up.", "start": 4655.665, "stop": 4656.602, "duration": 0.94}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, counsel.", "start": 4656.602, "stop": 4657.563, "duration": 0.96}, {"text": "Mr. Phillips, you have three minutes left.", "start": 4657.563, "stop": 4667.168, "duration": 9.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you Mr. Chief Justice, just a few points.", "start": 4667.168, "stop": 4669.741, "duration": 2.57}, {"text": "First of all, with respect to the state of the record and what was proffered and what was not proffered, if you look at the joint appendix at 2085, there is a specific proffer that is made by the Interveners in that context -- I mean, I'm sorry, there is a specific proffer made by the State of the --", "start": 4669.741, "stop": 4687.888, "duration": 18.15}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry, what page was that?", "start": 4687.888, "stop": 4689.561, "duration": 1.67}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "2085, that is volume 6 of it and it's at that point where the plaintiffs, the intervening plaintiffs say we would like to put on evidence of institutional violations, and Judge Karlton says twice this court has said, we will not receive that evidence.", "start": 4689.561, "stop": 4702.913, "duration": 13.35}, {"text": "You have made a clear -- as clear a record as you can; please don't waste our time and then later at 2338, which is again in volume 6, where we enter -- Mr. Desseimer, who is the assistant secretary of CDCR in charge of healthcare, he specifically said -- I've read this December declaration and it will not be received, to the extent that it says the State is in compliance.", "start": 4702.913, "stop": 4724.978, "duration": 22.07}, {"text": "So we have made our efforts and we were rebuffed.", "start": 4724.978, "stop": 4726.58, "duration": 1.6}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry; I don't know what the declaration said. Is the actual declaration in the record somewhere?", "start": 4726.58, "stop": 4731.707, "duration": 5.13}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I believe the actual declaration is in the record.", "start": 4731.707, "stop": 4734.389, "duration": 2.68}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "All right.", "start": 4734.389, "stop": 4734.969, "duration": 0.58}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Phillips, sorry, but I'm on a different subject.", "start": 4734.969, "stop": 4737.692, "duration": 2.72}, {"text": "Does the State stand by its representation that it can do this without any public safety impact in 5 years?", "start": 4737.692, "stop": 4745.883, "duration": 8.19}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 4745.883, "stop": 4746.27, "duration": 0.39}, {"text": "I mean, we made that submission to the court and we -- we believe that we could comply with it.", "start": 4746.27, "stop": 4750.599, "duration": 4.33}, {"text": "That said --", "start": 4750.599, "stop": 4750.926, "duration": 0.33}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "That means it's true.", "start": 4750.926, "stop": 4752.107, "duration": 1.18}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "We --", "start": 4752.107, "stop": 4752.771, "duration": 0.66}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "Not -- notwithstanding budget -- economic differences, budget differences?", "start": 4752.771, "stop": 4758.898, "duration": 6.13}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well -- well, I mean the plaintiff's counsel talks about all of the things that you had can do, and if you -- if you look at 70a of the -- the jurisdictional statement appendix, it specifically says, there is a line, above the line we can implement, and that will get you about 16,000 inmates and below the line you need legislation in order to implement these things.", "start": 4758.898, "stop": 4777.356, "duration": 18.46}, {"text": "But the reality is that anytime you say you are going to release 30,000 inmates in a very compressed period of time, I guarantee you that there is going to be more crime and people are going to die on the streets of California.", "start": 4777.356, "stop": 4788.903, "duration": 11.55}, {"text": "I mean that -- there is not way out of that particular box.", "start": 4788.903, "stop": 4791.623, "duration": 2.72}]}, {"speakerName": "Elena Kagan", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if they were 5 years you think you could do it without any public safety impact in the way that you told the court you could?", "start": 4791.623, "stop": 4797.487, "duration": 5.86}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think so, but I'm still concerned because the district court in this specific says, we have not evaluated the -- the safety impact of each of the State's -- of the elements the elements of the State's proposed plan, and it seems to me they had an obligation to do that.", "start": 4797.487, "stop": 4812.206, "duration": 14.72}, {"text": "The other point I want to make with respect to Justice Kennedy's question is that there is not a shred of evidence that 137.5 makes any sense whatsoever.", "start": 4812.206, "stop": 4819.531, "duration": 7.32}, {"text": "That is a pulled out of the air number.", "start": 4819.531, "stop": 4821.597, "duration": 2.07}, {"text": "Theirs was aspirational.", "start": 4821.597, "stop": 4823.622, "duration": 2.03}, {"text": "None of that is based on what is the constitutional violation that exists at the time you adopt that particular percentage.", "start": 4823.622, "stop": 4832.23, "duration": 8.61}, {"text": "And it seems to me this is the entire problem with this -- this exercise, which is to say we are going to fix this across the board, rather than what would make much more sense, which is to evaluate these matters facility by facility, to evaluate these matters on the basis of various discrete elements of how you can reduce the prison population, and to do it in -- in conjunction with a receiver who is in place who can help to implement this in a very systematic way and that will get us to where we want to get to.", "start": 4832.23, "stop": 4860.599, "duration": 28.37}]}, {"speakerName": "Sonia Sotomayor", "textObjs": [{"text": "So why didn't you give the court that as your plan?", "start": 4860.599, "stop": 4863.678, "duration": 3.08}, {"text": "The court gave you absolute discretion to implement the plan that you wanted.", "start": 4863.678, "stop": 4869.167, "duration": 5.49}, {"text": "It said we don't want to do facility by facility, because we want you to figure out where you need to implement.", "start": 4869.167, "stop": 4877.388, "duration": 8.22}, {"text": "So, your client didn't do that, why, either in your 5-year plan or in your 2-year plan?", "start": 4877.388, "stop": 4883.252, "duration": 5.86}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because the district court's order said you are going to have to reach 137.5 percent in two years.", "start": 4883.252, "stop": 4890.215, "duration": 6.96}, {"text": "That's the categorical rule, and the first time we went in to suggest something above 137 and a half, Judge Henderson said, \"I'm not hearing that\".", "start": 4890.215, "stop": 4897.641, "duration": 7.43}]}, {"speakerName": "John G. Roberts, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, counsel.", "start": 4897.641, "stop": 4898.289, "duration": 0.65}, {"text": "Mr. Phillips, Mr. Specter.", "start": 4898.289, "stop": 4899.648, "duration": 1.36}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 4899.648, "stop": 4901.773, "duration": 2.13}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Roberts Court", "arguedOn": "Nov 30, 2010", "petitioner": "", "respondent": "", "docket": "09-1233", "citation": "563 US 493 (2011)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/563/493", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit", "grantedOn": "Jun 14, 2010", "decidedOn": "May 23, 2011", "wikiData": {"title": "Brown v. Plata", "Litigants": "Brown v. Plata", "ArgueDate": "November 30", "ArgueYear": "2010", "DecideDate": "May 23", "DecideYear": "2011", "FullName": "Edmund G. Brown, Jr., Governor of California, et al., Appellants v. Marciano Plata, et al.", "USVol": "563", "USPage": "493", "ParallelCitations": "131 S. Ct. 1910; 179 [[L. Ed. 2d]] 969; 2011 [[U.S. LEXIS]] 4012", "Docket": "09-1233", "OralArgument": "", "OpinionAnnouncement": "https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/10pdf/09-1233.pdf", "Prior": "judgment for complainant sub nom. ''Coleman v. Wilson'', 912 [[F.Supp.]] 1282 ([[E.D. Cal.]], 1995); judgment for complainant sub nom. ''Plata v. Brown'', 3:01-cv-01351-TEH ([[N.D. Cal.]]n 2009).", "Subsequent": "", "Holding": "A court-mandated population limit was necessary to remedy a violation of prisoners' [[Eighth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Eighth Amendment]] constitutional rights.", "SCOTUS": "2010-2016", "Majority": "Kennedy", "JoinMajority": "Ginsburg, Breyer, Sotomayor, Kagan", "Dissent": "Scalia", "JoinDissent": "Thomas", "Dissent2": "Alito", "JoinDissent2": "Roberts", "LawsApplied": "[[Eighth Amendment to the United States Constitution|U.S. Const. amends. VIII]], [[Fourteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|XIV]]. [[Rehabilitation Act of 1973]], [[Prison Litigation Reform Act]], [[Americans With Disabilities Act]]"}}